WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.916 align:middle line:90%


00:00:06.916 --> 00:00:10.374 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:10.374 --> 00:00:27.700 align:middle line:90%


00:00:27.700 --> 00:00:30.200 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: Alongside
the Knights of the Round Table,

00:00:30.200 --> 00:00:33.620 align:middle line:10%
perhaps the next most intriguing
group of mystical gentleman

00:00:33.620 --> 00:00:35.080 align:middle line:10%
were the Knight Templar.

00:00:35.080 --> 00:00:37.100 align:middle line:84%
Freddy Silva has been
tracking their history

00:00:37.100 --> 00:00:38.630 align:middle line:90%
for more than a decade.

00:00:38.630 --> 00:00:41.420 align:middle line:10%
And has written a book
that is altering history--

00:00:41.420 --> 00:00:43.392 align:middle line:10%
the First Templar Nation.

00:00:43.392 --> 00:00:45.350 align:middle line:10%
We have spoken about the
Knight Templar before,

00:00:45.350 --> 00:00:47.930 align:middle line:10%
but now all the
threads come together.

00:00:47.930 --> 00:00:49.850 align:middle line:84%
All I can say Freddy
is, well done.

00:00:49.850 --> 00:00:51.590 align:middle line:90%
I mean, this was a massive work.

00:00:51.590 --> 00:00:53.280 align:middle line:90%
We were just talking off camera.

00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:56.420 align:middle line:84%
And there were times I could
only read 20 to 30 pages

00:00:56.420 --> 00:00:59.810 align:middle line:90%
in a day, because it's so rich.

00:00:59.810 --> 00:01:01.490 align:middle line:90%
It's like, OK, wait a minute.

00:01:01.490 --> 00:01:03.740 align:middle line:84%
If these guys were doing
this, and these guys

00:01:03.740 --> 00:01:06.210 align:middle line:84%
were doing that, what motivated
these guys to do that.

00:01:06.210 --> 00:01:07.010 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:01:07.010 --> 00:01:07.690 align:middle line:90%
>>FREDDY SILVA: Exactly.

00:01:07.690 --> 00:01:09.530 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean,
absolutely stunning work.

00:01:09.530 --> 00:01:09.770 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:01:09.770 --> 00:01:10.811 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Well, thank you.

00:01:10.811 --> 00:01:12.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --it has
taken over a decade.

00:01:12.890 --> 00:01:16.290 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I think I lost a lot
of my hair because of that.

00:01:16.290 --> 00:01:17.880 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Well, maybe.

00:01:17.880 --> 00:01:20.450 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I thought it was
something else, but no.

00:01:20.450 --> 00:01:21.540 align:middle line:90%
It was a very rich story.

00:01:21.540 --> 00:01:22.340 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:01:22.340 --> 00:01:23.600 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's an
incredible story.

00:01:23.600 --> 00:01:25.975 align:middle line:84%
And I'm intrigued with it for
a variety of reasons, which

00:01:25.975 --> 00:01:27.650 align:middle line:84%
is why we're going
to have a really

00:01:27.650 --> 00:01:30.540 align:middle line:84%
expansive talk about it that's
going to be in two parts.

00:01:30.540 --> 00:01:32.510 align:middle line:84%
So I just want to set
that up first off.

00:01:32.510 --> 00:01:33.510 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:01:33.510 --> 00:01:33.860 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: You're twisting my arm.

00:01:33.860 --> 00:01:36.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --we've seen
little bits of this story

00:01:36.290 --> 00:01:38.239 align:middle line:84%
in some of your other
work, as you were making

00:01:38.239 --> 00:01:39.530 align:middle line:90%
your discoveries along the way.

00:01:39.530 --> 00:01:39.890 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:01:39.890 --> 00:01:40.520 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Mm-hmm.

00:01:40.520 --> 00:01:41.960 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We would talk
about a piece of it here,

00:01:41.960 --> 00:01:43.250 align:middle line:90%
and a piece of it there.

00:01:43.250 --> 00:01:46.520 align:middle line:84%
And now, as I just said, all
the strings come together.

00:01:46.520 --> 00:01:47.320 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:01:47.320 --> 00:01:48.820 align:middle line:84%
I mean, originally
I was just trying

00:01:48.820 --> 00:01:50.930 align:middle line:84%
to write a very simple
book about the reason

00:01:50.930 --> 00:01:52.700 align:middle line:84%
why the Knights Templar
were so fascinated

00:01:52.700 --> 00:01:54.560 align:middle line:84%
with my original
country of birth,

00:01:54.560 --> 00:01:56.970 align:middle line:84%
which, of course by my
actions, it's Portugal.

00:01:56.970 --> 00:01:57.770 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Portugal.

00:01:57.770 --> 00:01:58.570 align:middle line:90%
Of course.

00:01:58.570 --> 00:02:01.290 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It's part of the
witness protection program.

00:02:01.290 --> 00:02:03.290 align:middle line:84%
And I thought this would
be a nice simple story.

00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:06.800 align:middle line:84%
And then I got to this big block
right in the middle of this.

00:02:06.800 --> 00:02:08.910 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, why am
I getting this block?

00:02:08.910 --> 00:02:12.407 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, I realized I don't
know part of the story here.

00:02:12.407 --> 00:02:13.490 align:middle line:90%
There's something missing.

00:02:13.490 --> 00:02:14.780 align:middle line:90%
A big piece of the story.

00:02:14.780 --> 00:02:18.590 align:middle line:84%
And it really had to do with the
understanding of sacred space,

00:02:18.590 --> 00:02:20.900 align:middle line:84%
which is something that is
something that's not always

00:02:20.900 --> 00:02:23.009 align:middle line:90%
associated with the Templars.

00:02:23.009 --> 00:02:25.550 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And once I understood
what sacred space really does,

00:02:25.550 --> 00:02:27.860 align:middle line:84%
and how it works, and what
the Templars have discovered

00:02:27.860 --> 00:02:28.740 align:middle line:90%
on to Jerusalem--

00:02:28.740 --> 00:02:29.540 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:02:29.540 --> 00:02:32.270 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: --then, suddenly
this big window of opportunity

00:02:32.270 --> 00:02:34.430 align:middle line:90%
opens up four years later.

00:02:34.430 --> 00:02:37.234 align:middle line:84%
And I go, well, that's
what I was missing.

00:02:37.234 --> 00:02:39.650 align:middle line:84%
Because now everything starts
to fit in very, very nicely.

00:02:39.650 --> 00:02:40.608 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You're right.

00:02:40.608 --> 00:02:42.067 align:middle line:84%
It has to do with
the sacred space.

00:02:42.067 --> 00:02:42.866 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:02:42.866 --> 00:02:45.260 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It has to do with
those incredibly divine

00:02:45.260 --> 00:02:47.900 align:middle line:84%
structures where
people have literally

00:02:47.900 --> 00:02:50.450 align:middle line:84%
consciousness-altering
experiences.

00:02:50.450 --> 00:02:51.560 align:middle line:90%
They were the masters.

00:02:51.560 --> 00:02:52.980 align:middle line:90%
They had the knowledge.

00:02:52.980 --> 00:02:54.980 align:middle line:84%
And I would argue, it's
been carried forward

00:02:54.980 --> 00:02:57.681 align:middle line:84%
this whole story
originated in Atlantis.

00:02:57.681 --> 00:02:59.180 align:middle line:84%
And we'll get into
that a little bit

00:02:59.180 --> 00:03:01.730 align:middle line:84%
later, because that's the
part that I love about it.

00:03:01.730 --> 00:03:06.410 align:middle line:84%
It's this continuation
of passed-on knowledge

00:03:06.410 --> 00:03:09.240 align:middle line:84%
that has been secreted away
throughout history until right

00:03:09.240 --> 00:03:10.040 align:middle line:90%
now, really.

00:03:10.040 --> 00:03:10.550 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, yeah.

00:03:10.550 --> 00:03:12.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You know, with
the explosion of media.

00:03:12.560 --> 00:03:14.930 align:middle line:84%
I think first, let's
start at this one place.

00:03:14.930 --> 00:03:16.640 align:middle line:84%
First of all, you
have these stories

00:03:16.640 --> 00:03:18.110 align:middle line:84%
that are just so
simplistic they're

00:03:18.110 --> 00:03:20.360 align:middle line:84%
like children's
fables, that are aired

00:03:20.360 --> 00:03:22.590 align:middle line:84%
on a lot of the networks
about the Templars.

00:03:22.590 --> 00:03:25.730 align:middle line:84%
It's just ridiculous to see how
they're still being portrayed.

00:03:25.730 --> 00:03:29.360 align:middle line:84%
And in light of your
book, it's absurd.

00:03:29.360 --> 00:03:32.120 align:middle line:84%
But still, in the
common mind you

00:03:32.120 --> 00:03:37.040 align:middle line:84%
have a feeling that these
were men of valor on one hand,

00:03:37.040 --> 00:03:38.660 align:middle line:84%
and the other
sentiment is that these

00:03:38.660 --> 00:03:41.330 align:middle line:90%
were bloody and greedy bankers.

00:03:41.330 --> 00:03:44.510 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
reducing it down.

00:03:44.510 --> 00:03:45.507 align:middle line:90%
What were they?

00:03:45.507 --> 00:03:47.840 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Well, I mean, that
was a part of the thing that

00:03:47.840 --> 00:03:51.680 align:middle line:84%
took so long to begin, which
was what I had the problem with.

00:03:51.680 --> 00:03:54.740 align:middle line:84%
Which was, yes, we see them
as bloodthirsty people,

00:03:54.740 --> 00:03:57.672 align:middle line:90%
as glory hounds, mercenaries.

00:03:57.672 --> 00:03:58.880 align:middle line:90%
Well, that was the crusaders.

00:03:58.880 --> 00:04:01.010 align:middle line:84%
The crusaders are
not the Templars.

00:04:01.010 --> 00:04:02.420 align:middle line:90%
And that was a big aha.

00:04:02.420 --> 00:04:04.755 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, once you get
to that point in the story,

00:04:04.755 --> 00:04:06.380 align:middle line:84%
you begin to realize
that this is going

00:04:06.380 --> 00:04:07.850 align:middle line:90%
to get really complicated.

00:04:07.850 --> 00:04:10.380 align:middle line:84%
Because what happened
wasn't the period.

00:04:10.380 --> 00:04:12.290 align:middle line:84%
We have a moment in
time where the church

00:04:12.290 --> 00:04:15.780 align:middle line:84%
is trying to get hold of
Jerusalem back from the Arabs.

00:04:15.780 --> 00:04:18.730 align:middle line:84%
This has been an ongoing
conflict forever.

00:04:18.730 --> 00:04:20.209 align:middle line:84%
And there was this
moment in time

00:04:20.209 --> 00:04:21.870 align:middle line:84%
where they had the
opportunity to actually get

00:04:21.870 --> 00:04:23.286 align:middle line:84%
a whole bunch of
people, convinced

00:04:23.286 --> 00:04:25.430 align:middle line:84%
them to go down to
Jerusalem, and literally

00:04:25.430 --> 00:04:26.960 align:middle line:90%
take over the place.

00:04:26.960 --> 00:04:31.520 align:middle line:84%
And it gave permission for
a small group of people,

00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:33.650 align:middle line:84%
a close group knit
of people to actually

00:04:33.650 --> 00:04:37.070 align:middle line:84%
ride on the back of the
Crusades, almost quietly,

00:04:37.070 --> 00:04:39.877 align:middle line:84%
and infiltrate the
Templars of Jerusalem.

00:04:39.877 --> 00:04:41.460 align:middle line:84%
And specific structures
in that city--

00:04:41.460 --> 00:04:42.260 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:04:42.260 --> 00:04:44.610 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: --in order to
do what they were doing.

00:04:44.610 --> 00:04:48.380 align:middle line:84%
I had no idea that there was
a kind of a moment in time

00:04:48.380 --> 00:04:51.110 align:middle line:84%
where they took the
opportunity to actually get

00:04:51.110 --> 00:04:54.405 align:middle line:84%
a handful of men in there
to do something very secret.

00:04:54.405 --> 00:04:56.030 align:middle line:84%
Nothing to do with
the Crusades at all.

00:04:56.030 --> 00:04:57.860 align:middle line:84%
It was basically
a means to an end.

00:04:57.860 --> 00:04:57.990 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And this is--

00:04:57.990 --> 00:04:58.989 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Very opportune.

00:04:58.989 --> 00:05:01.675 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I was going to say
at every point in the story--

00:05:01.675 --> 00:05:03.800 align:middle line:84%
and we're going to start
weaving the story together

00:05:03.800 --> 00:05:05.730 align:middle line:90%
in a moment--

00:05:05.730 --> 00:05:07.250 align:middle line:90%
there's opportunism.

00:05:07.250 --> 00:05:10.460 align:middle line:84%
And oftentimes the
opportunism is born out of--

00:05:10.460 --> 00:05:13.407 align:middle line:84%
there's always a need on the
part of one party or another.

00:05:13.407 --> 00:05:14.990 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's on the
part of the church

00:05:14.990 --> 00:05:17.150 align:middle line:84%
to stop the invasion
of the Arabs,

00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:19.340 align:middle line:84%
or whether it's the
same and among the royal

00:05:19.340 --> 00:05:21.760 align:middle line:84%
classes in various
countries, there

00:05:21.760 --> 00:05:24.740 align:middle line:90%
is a need that has to be met.

00:05:24.740 --> 00:05:30.490 align:middle line:84%
And these men, these Templars--
and we're going to talk about

00:05:30.490 --> 00:05:34.340 align:middle line:84%
the various kinds of
Templars there were--

00:05:34.340 --> 00:05:40.710 align:middle line:84%
really rode that opportunity in
many different ways, perfectly.

00:05:40.710 --> 00:05:41.510 align:middle line:90%
You're right.

00:05:41.510 --> 00:05:44.700 align:middle line:84%
It's almost as though they were
just sliding along the back of.

00:05:44.700 --> 00:05:47.900 align:middle line:84%
But yet they were right at
the middle of everything.

00:05:47.900 --> 00:05:50.780 align:middle line:84%
So first of all, let's talk
about how this story differs

00:05:50.780 --> 00:05:53.780 align:middle line:84%
from what we see on the History
Channel and other networks.

00:05:53.780 --> 00:05:55.758 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Well, that's
not too difficult.

00:05:55.758 --> 00:05:56.793 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:05:56.793 --> 00:05:59.790 align:middle line:10%
But basically, the
original story, of course,

00:05:59.790 --> 00:06:02.270 align:middle line:10%
is that nine guys
rode all the way

00:06:02.270 --> 00:06:05.360 align:middle line:10%
from what today is Belgium,
to go to the Middle East

00:06:05.360 --> 00:06:07.160 align:middle line:10%
to protect the pilgrims.

00:06:07.160 --> 00:06:08.930 align:middle line:10%
Now, you've got
a stretch of land

00:06:08.930 --> 00:06:11.900 align:middle line:10%
which is 33 miles,
filled with brigands,

00:06:11.900 --> 00:06:15.890 align:middle line:10%
mountain lions, Saracens,
other-- the very annoyed people

00:06:15.890 --> 00:06:18.410 align:middle line:10%
who don't like Europeans.

00:06:18.410 --> 00:06:21.180 align:middle line:84%
So you've got nine guys who are
patrolling tens of thousands

00:06:21.180 --> 00:06:21.980 align:middle line:90%
of pilgrims.

00:06:21.980 --> 00:06:24.950 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is a
ridiculous concept.

00:06:24.950 --> 00:06:28.250 align:middle line:84%
And also, historically-- yeah,
to take the sarcasm out of it,

00:06:28.250 --> 00:06:30.680 align:middle line:84%
historically, the
Knights Hospitaller,

00:06:30.680 --> 00:06:32.779 align:middle line:84%
which were already
40 years old by then,

00:06:32.779 --> 00:06:34.820 align:middle line:84%
they were already in charge
of doing that anyway.

00:06:34.820 --> 00:06:37.790 align:middle line:84%
So why do you need nine guys
to go and do what was already

00:06:37.790 --> 00:06:40.519 align:middle line:90%
being done by about 5,000?

00:06:40.519 --> 00:06:41.810 align:middle line:90%
And doing it very well as well.

00:06:41.810 --> 00:06:42.275 align:middle line:90%
Very efficiently.

00:06:42.275 --> 00:06:42.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:06:42.560 --> 00:06:44.601 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So the whole
thing is a big smokescreen.

00:06:44.601 --> 00:06:46.640 align:middle line:84%
I think it just got
taken out of context.

00:06:46.640 --> 00:06:49.181 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, I think we need
to also understand it weren't

00:06:49.181 --> 00:06:50.300 align:middle line:90%
just the Knight Templars.

00:06:50.300 --> 00:06:52.040 align:middle line:90%
You say "hos-pi-ta-llers"?

00:06:52.040 --> 00:06:53.340 align:middle line:90%
Or "hospi-ta-llers"?

00:06:53.340 --> 00:06:54.610 align:middle line:90%
How do you pronounce that?

00:06:54.610 --> 00:06:55.450 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: "hos-pi-ta-leur."

00:06:55.450 --> 00:06:55.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, "hos-pi-ta-leur."

00:06:55.870 --> 00:06:56.210 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:06:56.210 --> 00:06:57.010 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:06:57.010 --> 00:06:58.010 align:middle line:90%
So we have them.

00:06:58.010 --> 00:07:00.770 align:middle line:84%
We have the Order of
Sion Knights, right?

00:07:00.770 --> 00:07:03.230 align:middle line:10%
And we also have the Knights
of the Holy Sepulcher.

00:07:03.230 --> 00:07:06.050 align:middle line:84%
We have the Knights of Malta,
which most of us have heard of.

00:07:06.050 --> 00:07:07.510 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It sounds like
it's a Monty Python

00:07:07.510 --> 00:07:08.160 align:middle line:90%
movie really, doesn't it?

00:07:08.160 --> 00:07:08.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It really does.

00:07:08.750 --> 00:07:10.850 align:middle line:84%
But it all keeps getting
boiled down to the Knight

00:07:10.850 --> 00:07:12.040 align:middle line:90%
Templar, these nine guys.

00:07:12.040 --> 00:07:12.840 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yup.

00:07:12.840 --> 00:07:13.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right?

00:07:13.340 --> 00:07:14.270 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:07:14.270 --> 00:07:17.330 align:middle line:84%
And actually, all of these
people are all interconnected.

00:07:17.330 --> 00:07:18.870 align:middle line:84%
They're all
supporting each other.

00:07:18.870 --> 00:07:21.350 align:middle line:84%
And yes, originally
in about 1904--

00:07:21.350 --> 00:07:23.750 align:middle line:84%
not 1904-- 1104--
there was a group

00:07:23.750 --> 00:07:27.140 align:middle line:84%
of people who did join the
Holy Sepulcher, where Hugues de

00:07:27.140 --> 00:07:29.180 align:middle line:84%
Payens, and Godfrey
de Saint-Omer,

00:07:29.180 --> 00:07:32.830 align:middle line:84%
the nucleus of what became
the Templars, were residing.

00:07:32.830 --> 00:07:34.580 align:middle line:84%
And I think they tried
to start something.

00:07:34.580 --> 00:07:36.440 align:middle line:84%
And I was reading a
lot of the surviving

00:07:36.440 --> 00:07:37.486 align:middle line:90%
extracts from the time.

00:07:37.486 --> 00:07:39.110 align:middle line:84%
And they were having
a really hard time

00:07:39.110 --> 00:07:41.270 align:middle line:84%
trying to recruit the
right kind of knight

00:07:41.270 --> 00:07:43.160 align:middle line:90%
to do something very important.

00:07:43.160 --> 00:07:46.191 align:middle line:84%
Because you keep reading between
the lines, and Hugues de Payens

00:07:46.191 --> 00:07:47.690 align:middle line:84%
was really struggling
to find people

00:07:47.690 --> 00:07:50.000 align:middle line:84%
who had certain spiritual
angle on things.

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:51.620 align:middle line:84%
They weren't there
to do any fighting.

00:07:51.620 --> 00:07:53.400 align:middle line:84%
They rarely did any
fighting at all--

00:07:53.400 --> 00:07:54.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:07:54.200 --> 00:07:54.980 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: --which
was kind of odd.

00:07:54.980 --> 00:07:55.850 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:07:55.850 --> 00:07:59.960 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Why would a
bunch of very rich people

00:07:59.960 --> 00:08:04.040 align:middle line:84%
go 2000 miles to the Middle East
and then not do any fighting,

00:08:04.040 --> 00:08:05.690 align:middle line:84%
and also give up
all their wealth

00:08:05.690 --> 00:08:06.812 align:middle line:90%
to go and look for wealth?

00:08:06.812 --> 00:08:07.770 align:middle line:90%
Doesn't make any sense.

00:08:07.770 --> 00:08:08.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:08:08.300 --> 00:08:10.008 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And you'd
have to dig up tunnels

00:08:10.008 --> 00:08:12.590 align:middle line:84%
as well in
excruciating conditions

00:08:12.590 --> 00:08:14.811 align:middle line:90%
to find this alleged wealth.

00:08:14.811 --> 00:08:16.310 align:middle line:84%
The whole thing
just doesn't add up.

00:08:16.310 --> 00:08:16.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:08:16.830 --> 00:08:19.371 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So you have a group,
which is the Knight of the Holy

00:08:19.371 --> 00:08:22.130 align:middle line:84%
Sepulcher, moving in
just at the time when

00:08:22.130 --> 00:08:23.420 align:middle line:90%
Jerusalem is liberated.

00:08:23.420 --> 00:08:26.060 align:middle line:84%
At the same time,
you had the patriarch

00:08:26.060 --> 00:08:29.120 align:middle line:84%
of Jerusalem, Godfrey de
Bouillon, who basically

00:08:29.120 --> 00:08:30.560 align:middle line:84%
installed another
group of knights

00:08:30.560 --> 00:08:34.320 align:middle line:84%
in the Church of the
Sion, or Mount Sion,

00:08:34.320 --> 00:08:36.169 align:middle line:90%
in a ruined basilica.

00:08:36.169 --> 00:08:38.090 align:middle line:84%
And then you have
another group of people,

00:08:38.090 --> 00:08:41.780 align:middle line:84%
who are just basically going
in-between connecting the dots.

00:08:41.780 --> 00:08:44.090 align:middle line:84%
So it is excruciatingly
difficult

00:08:44.090 --> 00:08:46.900 align:middle line:84%
to separate all those people
and find out in the end,

00:08:46.900 --> 00:08:48.740 align:middle line:84%
they were all kind
of collaborating.

00:08:48.740 --> 00:08:51.230 align:middle line:84%
But still, they had nothing
to do with the Crusades.

00:08:51.230 --> 00:08:52.820 align:middle line:84%
It was basically a
big moment in time,

00:08:52.820 --> 00:08:54.410 align:middle line:90%
a big window of opportunity.

00:08:54.410 --> 00:08:58.550 align:middle line:84%
As though some organization had
been waiting for 1,000 years

00:08:58.550 --> 00:09:02.450 align:middle line:84%
to finish what the Assyrians
had started and finished when

00:09:02.450 --> 00:09:03.890 align:middle line:90%
the Romans invaded Jerusalem.

00:09:03.890 --> 00:09:05.540 align:middle line:84%
And that's really what
the story goes back to.

00:09:05.540 --> 00:09:05.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:09:05.780 --> 00:09:07.160 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: 2000 years earlier.

00:09:07.160 --> 00:09:10.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So before we
go there, let's go back

00:09:10.280 --> 00:09:11.980 align:middle line:90%
just a little bit further.

00:09:11.980 --> 00:09:16.160 align:middle line:84%
And let's go back into the
period you're talking about,

00:09:16.160 --> 00:09:19.640 align:middle line:84%
where Burgundy was actually
the center of enlightenment.

00:09:19.640 --> 00:09:21.890 align:middle line:84%
Because this is not
something most people

00:09:21.890 --> 00:09:24.080 align:middle line:84%
are aware of when we think
of the Enlightenment.

00:09:24.080 --> 00:09:27.320 align:middle line:84%
So let's just start
pulling threads together.

00:09:27.320 --> 00:09:30.170 align:middle line:84%
And I know people have to
read the book and sit with it,

00:09:30.170 --> 00:09:31.100 align:middle line:90%
and re--

00:09:31.100 --> 00:09:32.570 align:middle line:84%
just have it as
their companion--

00:09:32.570 --> 00:09:34.550 align:middle line:84%
their historical
companion for a while--

00:09:34.550 --> 00:09:35.415 align:middle line:90%
to do this well.

00:09:35.415 --> 00:09:36.540 align:middle line:90%
But we're going to attempt.

00:09:36.540 --> 00:09:38.750 align:middle line:10%
So let's go back to
Burgundy and what

00:09:38.750 --> 00:09:40.260 align:middle line:10%
was happening with Burgundy.

00:09:40.260 --> 00:09:44.870 align:middle line:10%
And from there, let's segue
into the Merovingian bloodline.

00:09:44.870 --> 00:09:45.670 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:09:45.670 --> 00:09:47.090 align:middle line:84%
The time period
we're dealing with

00:09:47.090 --> 00:09:50.690 align:middle line:84%
is about the end of the
10th century, 11th century.

00:09:50.690 --> 00:09:52.766 align:middle line:90%
And Europe is a complete mess.

00:09:52.766 --> 00:09:54.890 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's people
fighting all over the place.

00:09:54.890 --> 00:09:57.270 align:middle line:84%
It's an economy
based on plunder.

00:09:57.270 --> 00:09:59.020 align:middle line:84%
Even families are at
each other's throats.

00:09:59.020 --> 00:09:59.220 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Barbaric.

00:09:59.220 --> 00:10:00.590 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: It was really barbaric.

00:10:00.590 --> 00:10:01.870 align:middle line:84%
And some of the things
that they were up to

00:10:01.870 --> 00:10:03.380 align:middle line:84%
are kind of left
out and edited out.

00:10:03.380 --> 00:10:05.512 align:middle line:84%
Because it was entertaining,
but after a while

00:10:05.512 --> 00:10:06.470 align:middle line:90%
it gets a bit gruesome.

00:10:06.470 --> 00:10:08.750 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, we'll get into
a couple of them just to kind

00:10:08.750 --> 00:10:09.560 align:middle line:90%
of set the stage--

00:10:09.560 --> 00:10:10.200 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Because it's fun.

00:10:10.200 --> 00:10:11.116 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: --for color.

00:10:11.116 --> 00:10:12.072 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:10:12.072 --> 00:10:13.580 align:middle line:90%
A lot of color.

00:10:13.580 --> 00:10:18.200 align:middle line:84%
And basically, you had this
nucleus of productivity

00:10:18.200 --> 00:10:20.609 align:middle line:84%
where intellectualism
was allowed to flourish.

00:10:20.609 --> 00:10:22.400 align:middle line:84%
In the middle of this
you've got the church

00:10:22.400 --> 00:10:24.800 align:middle line:84%
that's now become the
main strongman of Europe,

00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:26.520 align:middle line:84%
trying to keep down
anything that's

00:10:26.520 --> 00:10:27.990 align:middle line:90%
intellectual or spiritual.

00:10:27.990 --> 00:10:30.620 align:middle line:84%
Because they have a
monopoly on all that stuff.

00:10:30.620 --> 00:10:32.310 align:middle line:84%
They don't want anybody
else to compete.

00:10:32.310 --> 00:10:35.070 align:middle line:84%
So suddenly in Burgundy
you have this sort

00:10:35.070 --> 00:10:36.960 align:middle line:84%
of modicum of
enlightenment going on,

00:10:36.960 --> 00:10:39.420 align:middle line:84%
a renaissance in this
tiny, little county

00:10:39.420 --> 00:10:41.250 align:middle line:90%
in what is today France.

00:10:41.250 --> 00:10:44.340 align:middle line:84%
And here you have the background
of all the people, all

00:10:44.340 --> 00:10:46.770 align:middle line:84%
the families, that
do eventually become

00:10:46.770 --> 00:10:49.860 align:middle line:84%
the main players of the
Templar drama, who are also,

00:10:49.860 --> 00:10:51.690 align:middle line:84%
of course, related
to the Cistercians,

00:10:51.690 --> 00:10:53.255 align:middle line:84%
who have yet to
come on the scene.

00:10:53.255 --> 00:10:54.630 align:middle line:84%
And all of these
people, when you

00:10:54.630 --> 00:10:56.760 align:middle line:84%
start looking at the
alliances, and what

00:10:56.760 --> 00:10:59.220 align:middle line:84%
they were doing in
Burgundy in that time,

00:10:59.220 --> 00:11:01.910 align:middle line:84%
they're setting up centers of
education of enlightenment.

00:11:01.910 --> 00:11:03.390 align:middle line:90%
They were even working--

00:11:03.390 --> 00:11:05.940 align:middle line:84%
they had Arabs and Hebrews
working side by side.

00:11:05.940 --> 00:11:07.350 align:middle line:90%
God help us.

00:11:07.350 --> 00:11:08.950 align:middle line:84%
Everybody was in
on the same thing.

00:11:08.950 --> 00:11:10.920 align:middle line:84%
They were looking for
something much more than

00:11:10.920 --> 00:11:14.430 align:middle line:84%
was being provided for by
spiritual people at the time--

00:11:14.430 --> 00:11:16.120 align:middle line:90%
religious people at the time.

00:11:16.120 --> 00:11:18.510 align:middle line:84%
So they're forming their
own little sort of bulwark

00:11:18.510 --> 00:11:20.970 align:middle line:90%
against barbarity at the time.

00:11:20.970 --> 00:11:22.680 align:middle line:84%
And in the middle of
all of this you also

00:11:22.680 --> 00:11:25.260 align:middle line:84%
have people who are associated
with a very old bloodline

00:11:25.260 --> 00:11:28.740 align:middle line:84%
called the Merovingians, who
are now traced all the way back

00:11:28.740 --> 00:11:29.940 align:middle line:90%
to Sumeria.

00:11:29.940 --> 00:11:33.210 align:middle line:84%
And before that-- and we're
now talking a stretch of 6,000

00:11:33.210 --> 00:11:34.230 align:middle line:90%
years--

00:11:34.230 --> 00:11:37.691 align:middle line:84%
to the bloodline of the Scythian
culture, who was predominately

00:11:37.691 --> 00:11:39.690 align:middle line:84%
living around the Black
Sea, in what today would

00:11:39.690 --> 00:11:42.030 align:middle line:90%
be a Transylvania and Bulgaria.

00:11:42.030 --> 00:11:43.920 align:middle line:84%
And there is a
connection to Dracula,

00:11:43.920 --> 00:11:47.760 align:middle line:84%
which we might get into, but
it's a little of a sidestep.

00:11:47.760 --> 00:11:51.690 align:middle line:84%
So this bloodline apparently
came from a divine source.

00:11:51.690 --> 00:11:53.520 align:middle line:84%
It was said to come
originally from people

00:11:53.520 --> 00:11:55.620 align:middle line:84%
who are half human,
half divine, that

00:11:55.620 --> 00:11:58.520 align:middle line:84%
survived the huge catastrophe
on the face of the Earth 11,000

00:11:58.520 --> 00:11:59.320 align:middle line:90%
years ago.

00:11:59.320 --> 00:12:02.880 align:middle line:84%
And by intermarrying
within their own kind,

00:12:02.880 --> 00:12:05.910 align:middle line:84%
they kept this bloodline pure
for the Sumerian bloodline,

00:12:05.910 --> 00:12:07.440 align:middle line:90%
for the Troy bloodline.

00:12:07.440 --> 00:12:09.750 align:middle line:84%
And eventually they
got into Europe,

00:12:09.750 --> 00:12:11.390 align:middle line:90%
and to the Merovingians.

00:12:11.390 --> 00:12:13.806 align:middle line:84%
And it literally-- the reason
why they wanted to keep this

00:12:13.806 --> 00:12:16.290 align:middle line:84%
bloodline pure is because
a lot of these rulers--

00:12:16.290 --> 00:12:18.040 align:middle line:90%
and there was men and women--

00:12:18.040 --> 00:12:21.360 align:middle line:84%
they were associated
with being great healers.

00:12:21.360 --> 00:12:23.410 align:middle line:90%
They had the ability to see far.

00:12:23.410 --> 00:12:27.489 align:middle line:84%
In other words, they had
the ability to be psychics.

00:12:27.489 --> 00:12:28.530 align:middle line:90%
They were great teachers.

00:12:28.530 --> 00:12:30.772 align:middle line:84%
They believed in improving
people's lot on the land.

00:12:30.772 --> 00:12:32.730 align:middle line:84%
They would teach people
how to raise themselves

00:12:32.730 --> 00:12:36.240 align:middle line:84%
from a very basic, then
sustainable level, to really

00:12:36.240 --> 00:12:37.780 align:middle line:90%
empowering themselves.

00:12:37.780 --> 00:12:40.560 align:middle line:84%
So of course, in the middle of
all of this drudgery in Europe,

00:12:40.560 --> 00:12:45.040 align:middle line:84%
and this extraordinary control
by the Catholic Church,

00:12:45.040 --> 00:12:47.530 align:middle line:90%
this was like manna from heaven.

00:12:47.530 --> 00:12:49.470 align:middle line:84%
The Merovingians were
absolutely adored,

00:12:49.470 --> 00:12:51.120 align:middle line:90%
as far as I can figure out.

00:12:51.120 --> 00:12:54.540 align:middle line:84%
And it's from this basis
that we get the central group

00:12:54.540 --> 00:12:57.370 align:middle line:84%
of families in Burgundy that
then become the people who

00:12:57.370 --> 00:13:00.120 align:middle line:84%
become the supporters
of the nation, Knights

00:13:00.120 --> 00:13:02.760 align:middle line:84%
Templar, and all of
their people around it.

00:13:02.760 --> 00:13:04.220 align:middle line:90%
So it's a very complex story.

00:13:04.220 --> 00:13:06.300 align:middle line:84%
But it goes back
thousands of years

00:13:06.300 --> 00:13:08.610 align:middle line:84%
to a plan that was
laid down before,

00:13:08.610 --> 00:13:11.460 align:middle line:84%
that really it was nothing
more than just raising people

00:13:11.460 --> 00:13:14.140 align:middle line:84%
from a state of barbarity
into being highly enlightened.

00:13:14.140 --> 00:13:16.060 align:middle line:84%
Kind of what we're
looking for today.

00:13:16.060 --> 00:13:16.860 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:13:16.860 --> 00:13:19.680 align:middle line:84%
Well-- and I would even argue
the same players keep emerging

00:13:19.680 --> 00:13:21.132 align:middle line:90%
over, and over, and over.

00:13:21.132 --> 00:13:22.340 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: It makes you wonder.

00:13:22.340 --> 00:13:24.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Well, because I have--

00:13:24.870 --> 00:13:27.090 align:middle line:84%
like most of the
planet, I'm very

00:13:27.090 --> 00:13:29.490 align:middle line:84%
comfortable with the
notion of reincarnation.

00:13:29.490 --> 00:13:34.130 align:middle line:84%
And certain souls have
certain abilities and tasks

00:13:34.130 --> 00:13:36.600 align:middle line:84%
that they carry forward
from time to time.

00:13:36.600 --> 00:13:38.700 align:middle line:90%
And certainly our DNA follow--

00:13:38.700 --> 00:13:43.650 align:middle line:84%
our incarnation patterns
are affected by our DNA.

00:13:43.650 --> 00:13:45.060 align:middle line:90%
And we follow DNA lineages.

00:13:45.060 --> 00:13:46.060 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, I think so.

00:13:46.060 --> 00:13:48.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So if we're looking
at it through that lens that I

00:13:48.560 --> 00:13:50.880 align:middle line:84%
look at it through,
we're looking at it

00:13:50.880 --> 00:13:55.200 align:middle line:84%
as a continuation of knowledge
being inculcated on the planet

00:13:55.200 --> 00:13:58.020 align:middle line:84%
Earth, from beings
that have probably

00:13:58.020 --> 00:14:01.380 align:middle line:84%
been here well
toward the beginning,

00:14:01.380 --> 00:14:05.670 align:middle line:84%
to try to continue to
enlighten during dark times.

00:14:05.670 --> 00:14:08.190 align:middle line:84%
And uphold certain
knowledge, and inculcate it

00:14:08.190 --> 00:14:10.677 align:middle line:84%
into the population
wherever they incarnate.

00:14:10.677 --> 00:14:13.052 align:middle line:84%
And it sounds like that was
the richest place to do this.

00:14:13.052 --> 00:14:14.052 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, absolutely.

00:14:14.052 --> 00:14:15.750 align:middle line:84%
And the more you go
into ancient myth,

00:14:15.750 --> 00:14:17.416 align:middle line:84%
the more it becomes
obvious that there's

00:14:17.416 --> 00:14:18.727 align:middle line:90%
a pattern going on here.

00:14:18.727 --> 00:14:21.060 align:middle line:84%
And it's something I'm working
on at the moment as well.

00:14:21.060 --> 00:14:23.250 align:middle line:84%
Looking at myths from the
point of view of a very--

00:14:23.250 --> 00:14:24.435 align:middle line:90%
extremely ancient culture.

00:14:24.435 --> 00:14:26.700 align:middle line:84%
It's going back to a
time before the flood.

00:14:26.700 --> 00:14:27.870 align:middle line:90%
So with the--

00:14:27.870 --> 00:14:29.020 align:middle line:90%
11,000 years ago.

00:14:29.020 --> 00:14:29.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:14:29.820 --> 00:14:31.830 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And there is
this recurring connection,

00:14:31.830 --> 00:14:34.890 align:middle line:84%
this thread that runs
right in the center

00:14:34.890 --> 00:14:38.430 align:middle line:84%
of this extraordinary place
we call Earth and humanity,

00:14:38.430 --> 00:14:41.841 align:middle line:84%
which is a big playground
for creativity and stupidity.

00:14:41.841 --> 00:14:43.632 align:middle line:84%
And they kind of go
hand in hand down here.

00:14:43.632 --> 00:14:45.090 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And when there's
too much stupidity,

00:14:45.090 --> 00:14:47.410 align:middle line:84%
these same beings continue
coming back and saying,

00:14:47.410 --> 00:14:48.640 align:middle line:90%
OK, guys.

00:14:48.640 --> 00:14:49.652 align:middle line:90%
Time to wake up again.

00:14:49.652 --> 00:14:50.985 align:middle line:90%
Let's see the little knowledge--

00:14:50.985 --> 00:14:51.221 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Been there.

00:14:51.221 --> 00:14:53.020 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --until you
screw it up again.

00:14:53.020 --> 00:14:54.500 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And they keep
changing their name.

00:14:54.500 --> 00:14:55.735 align:middle line:90%
It's like a big PR exercise.

00:14:55.735 --> 00:14:58.320 align:middle line:84%
It's just like, well, we can't
call ourselves that anymore,

00:14:58.320 --> 00:15:00.819 align:middle line:84%
because we know what happened
when we called ourselves that.

00:15:00.819 --> 00:15:02.400 align:middle line:84%
Someone came along
and killed us all.

00:15:02.400 --> 00:15:04.890 align:middle line:84%
So we come back
again into the body,

00:15:04.890 --> 00:15:07.555 align:middle line:84%
and we now go and call
ourselves something else.

00:15:07.555 --> 00:15:08.805 align:middle line:90%
So it's actually quite clever.

00:15:08.805 --> 00:15:09.971 align:middle line:90%
It's almost like a big joke.

00:15:09.971 --> 00:15:12.690 align:middle line:84%
If you just step away from the
historical angle, and see that,

00:15:12.690 --> 00:15:13.490 align:middle line:90%
yes.

00:15:13.490 --> 00:15:15.840 align:middle line:84%
There are recurrences where
the same characters appear

00:15:15.840 --> 00:15:18.180 align:middle line:84%
to be repeating themselves
again, and again, and again.

00:15:18.180 --> 00:15:18.880 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And again.

00:15:18.880 --> 00:15:20.970 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And following the
work of Michael Newton,

00:15:20.970 --> 00:15:24.330 align:middle line:84%
the psychoanalyst in LA, who
wrote two of the best books

00:15:24.330 --> 00:15:26.847 align:middle line:84%
on reincarnation and
life between lives--

00:15:26.847 --> 00:15:28.930 align:middle line:84%
we're talking about a
clinical psychologist that's

00:15:28.930 --> 00:15:31.150 align:middle line:90%
really going to new-age stuff.

00:15:31.150 --> 00:15:32.210 align:middle line:90%
He's not into woo-woo.

00:15:32.210 --> 00:15:33.975 align:middle line:84%
He's a literal
clinical psychologist

00:15:33.975 --> 00:15:37.340 align:middle line:84%
that deals with drinking
problems, sexual addiction, all

00:15:37.340 --> 00:15:38.140 align:middle line:90%
that stuff.

00:15:38.140 --> 00:15:39.220 align:middle line:90%
Sit on my couch.

00:15:39.220 --> 00:15:40.579 align:middle line:90%
We'll count to 10.

00:15:40.579 --> 00:15:42.870 align:middle line:84%
And when you come back to
one I will suggest something.

00:15:42.870 --> 00:15:43.910 align:middle line:90%
And you're cured.

00:15:43.910 --> 00:15:45.820 align:middle line:10%
And to his surprise,
the patients

00:15:45.820 --> 00:15:47.620 align:middle line:10%
were describing
what was happening

00:15:47.620 --> 00:15:50.590 align:middle line:10%
on the other side of the veil,
in-between lives, and also

00:15:50.590 --> 00:15:51.470 align:middle line:10%
reincarnation.

00:15:51.470 --> 00:15:54.140 align:middle line:10%
And the next patient would
pick up the story, entranced.

00:15:54.140 --> 00:15:54.940 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:15:54.940 --> 00:15:55.578 align:middle line:10%
>>SILVA: Extraordinary material.

00:15:55.578 --> 00:15:56.070 align:middle line:10%
And it's great relegation.

00:15:56.070 --> 00:15:57.370 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: It is extraordinary.

00:15:57.370 --> 00:15:59.860 align:middle line:84%
And I've witnessed it, and
experienced it a great deal

00:15:59.860 --> 00:16:03.070 align:middle line:84%
myself, as I had a
therapy clinic years ago.

00:16:03.070 --> 00:16:04.600 align:middle line:90%
And my specialty was regression.

00:16:04.600 --> 00:16:05.080 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, really?

00:16:05.080 --> 00:16:05.880 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And yeah.

00:16:05.880 --> 00:16:07.510 align:middle line:84%
Because I started
seeing these problems

00:16:07.510 --> 00:16:10.135 align:middle line:84%
kept continuing back with people
who were open and spontaneous.

00:16:10.135 --> 00:16:12.370 align:middle line:84%
That they were suddenly
somewhere-- not

00:16:12.370 --> 00:16:13.360 align:middle line:90%
where we were anyway.

00:16:13.360 --> 00:16:14.920 align:middle line:90%
Not at this period of time.

00:16:14.920 --> 00:16:17.950 align:middle line:84%
But you'd start seeing
something like what

00:16:17.950 --> 00:16:21.800 align:middle line:84%
you were talking about, where
one person would come in

00:16:21.800 --> 00:16:22.600 align:middle line:90%
with a--

00:16:22.600 --> 00:16:25.180 align:middle line:84%
it's usually a common
malady of some kind.

00:16:25.180 --> 00:16:27.460 align:middle line:84%
And you start peeling
back the layers,

00:16:27.460 --> 00:16:29.560 align:middle line:84%
and they pop back
to this other time.

00:16:29.560 --> 00:16:32.870 align:middle line:84%
Maybe a week or two, or a month
later, another person comes in.

00:16:32.870 --> 00:16:34.660 align:middle line:84%
Their story's
cross-validating that.

00:16:34.660 --> 00:16:35.890 align:middle line:90%
They don't know each other.

00:16:35.890 --> 00:16:38.800 align:middle line:84%
This happens-- anyone that
does regression work sees this.

00:16:38.800 --> 00:16:42.790 align:middle line:84%
These stories-- you start
getting a very complex web,

00:16:42.790 --> 00:16:46.270 align:middle line:84%
that actually starts reducing
to being able to discern.

00:16:46.270 --> 00:16:48.560 align:middle line:90%
Certain periods of history.

00:16:48.560 --> 00:16:50.860 align:middle line:84%
Certain things that were
happening at certain points

00:16:50.860 --> 00:16:52.860 align:middle line:90%
on the planet at a given time.

00:16:52.860 --> 00:16:55.720 align:middle line:84%
And there's a lot of
cross-validation for this.

00:16:55.720 --> 00:16:59.020 align:middle line:84%
So I bring it up because I
couldn't look at your story

00:16:59.020 --> 00:17:01.660 align:middle line:84%
without looking at
it through that lens.

00:17:01.660 --> 00:17:02.560 align:middle line:90%
Because it was just--

00:17:02.560 --> 00:17:02.860 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I think
it's a good point.

00:17:02.860 --> 00:17:04.329 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: --too familiar.

00:17:04.329 --> 00:17:08.589 align:middle line:84%
And so if you take all of these,
pre-Diluvian times and such--

00:17:08.589 --> 00:17:14.020 align:middle line:84%
again, back to the first
civilizations of Atlantis,

00:17:14.020 --> 00:17:17.109 align:middle line:84%
the early Atlantean
civilizations-- technology

00:17:17.109 --> 00:17:18.250 align:middle line:90%
was high.

00:17:18.250 --> 00:17:20.780 align:middle line:90%
Initially very peaceful times.

00:17:20.780 --> 00:17:23.410 align:middle line:84%
You were talking about a
great understanding of all

00:17:23.410 --> 00:17:25.420 align:middle line:90%
of these arts and sciences.

00:17:25.420 --> 00:17:26.899 align:middle line:90%
It didn't go away.

00:17:26.899 --> 00:17:29.315 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And it also ended up
in a very bad place as well.

00:17:29.315 --> 00:17:29.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: They did end up--

00:17:29.610 --> 00:17:31.870 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And it always ends
up going left in Albuquerque.

00:17:31.870 --> 00:17:34.036 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, I mean
that's a long period of time.

00:17:34.036 --> 00:17:36.282 align:middle line:84%
And then if we understand
that history is also

00:17:36.282 --> 00:17:37.990 align:middle line:84%
running concurrently,
we don't understand

00:17:37.990 --> 00:17:40.450 align:middle line:84%
the time frames of history
of our cultures right now.

00:17:40.450 --> 00:17:40.600 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:17:40.600 --> 00:17:42.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean, if
you look at Egypt,

00:17:42.430 --> 00:17:45.640 align:middle line:84%
if it's true that Egypt actually
dates back 200,000 years,

00:17:45.640 --> 00:17:47.020 align:middle line:90%
it was concurrent with Atlantis.

00:17:47.020 --> 00:17:49.470 align:middle line:84%
So this knowledge was
always being seeded.

00:17:49.470 --> 00:17:50.270 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:17:50.270 --> 00:17:50.550 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right?

00:17:50.550 --> 00:17:50.830 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:17:50.830 --> 00:17:52.663 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: There was
emigration all the time,

00:17:52.663 --> 00:17:56.060 align:middle line:84%
including to Burgundy,
ultimately Portugal.

00:17:56.060 --> 00:17:56.860 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:17:56.860 --> 00:17:58.687 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Jerusalem.

00:17:58.687 --> 00:18:00.520 align:middle line:84%
So we're going to talk
modern history, which

00:18:00.520 --> 00:18:01.890 align:middle line:90%
is just the last 1,000 years.

00:18:01.890 --> 00:18:02.690 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:18:02.690 --> 00:18:04.106 align:middle line:84%
In fact, if you
actually take away

00:18:04.106 --> 00:18:06.580 align:middle line:84%
the names of the various
players, like the Templars,

00:18:06.580 --> 00:18:08.380 align:middle line:84%
or the Essenes, or
the Cistercians,

00:18:08.380 --> 00:18:10.630 align:middle line:84%
you find that they're
actually the same people.

00:18:10.630 --> 00:18:12.320 align:middle line:84%
You'd be talking about the
same people all the time.

00:18:12.320 --> 00:18:13.480 align:middle line:90%
They would dress the same way.

00:18:13.480 --> 00:18:14.620 align:middle line:90%
They behaved the same way.

00:18:14.620 --> 00:18:16.810 align:middle line:84%
They believed in the
same belief systems.

00:18:16.810 --> 00:18:20.350 align:middle line:84%
They acted it towards a
certain predetermined goal.

00:18:20.350 --> 00:18:21.460 align:middle line:90%
You can't tell them apart.

00:18:21.460 --> 00:18:23.290 align:middle line:90%
So it seems to me that, yes--

00:18:23.290 --> 00:18:26.260 align:middle line:84%
there is some part of me that
says, yes, there is something

00:18:26.260 --> 00:18:28.330 align:middle line:84%
that as though these
people came back to finish

00:18:28.330 --> 00:18:30.170 align:middle line:90%
a job from 1,000 years ago.

00:18:30.170 --> 00:18:30.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And that makes sense.

00:18:30.730 --> 00:18:31.570 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It's a
pretty romantic idea,

00:18:31.570 --> 00:18:32.290 align:middle line:90%
but it makes sense as well.

00:18:32.290 --> 00:18:34.600 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, it's just
logical, in my opinion.

00:18:34.600 --> 00:18:39.070 align:middle line:84%
And also we have to add
into that blend the Celts

00:18:39.070 --> 00:18:40.700 align:middle line:90%
and the Druids.

00:18:40.700 --> 00:18:41.500 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:18:41.500 --> 00:18:42.070 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:18:42.070 --> 00:18:43.457 align:middle line:84%
All part of the same
tree of knowledge.

00:18:43.457 --> 00:18:43.590 align:middle line:90%
Same branch.

00:18:43.590 --> 00:18:45.631 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: All part of the
same tree of knowledge,

00:18:45.631 --> 00:18:48.100 align:middle line:84%
bringing forward the same
knowledge over and over

00:18:48.100 --> 00:18:49.180 align:middle line:90%
when times are dark.

00:18:49.180 --> 00:18:49.510 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:18:49.510 --> 00:18:50.260 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:18:50.260 --> 00:18:52.134 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Or when times
are about to go dark,

00:18:52.134 --> 00:18:55.390 align:middle line:84%
to try to reestablish it
in the minds of people

00:18:55.390 --> 00:18:56.590 align:middle line:90%
before the lights go out.

00:18:56.590 --> 00:18:57.010 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:18:57.010 --> 00:18:59.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So that's these
cycles of consciousness.

00:18:59.170 --> 00:19:01.905 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they have other words
for it in other traditions.

00:19:01.905 --> 00:19:02.180 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:19:02.180 --> 00:19:03.040 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Which is,
by the way, they

00:19:03.040 --> 00:19:04.630 align:middle line:84%
keep changing their
names all the time.

00:19:04.630 --> 00:19:04.975 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:19:04.975 --> 00:19:05.990 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: It's like a company.

00:19:05.990 --> 00:19:07.510 align:middle line:84%
It's like, well, that
didn't work out so well.

00:19:07.510 --> 00:19:07.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:19:07.900 --> 00:19:08.770 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Let's change our
name to something else.

00:19:08.770 --> 00:19:10.090 align:middle line:90%
That will work.

00:19:10.090 --> 00:19:10.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:19:10.940 --> 00:19:11.740 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:19:11.740 --> 00:19:14.280 align:middle line:90%
So now let's return to--

00:19:14.280 --> 00:19:17.260 align:middle line:84%
we've set up a little bit about
what was happening in Burgundy.

00:19:17.260 --> 00:19:19.630 align:middle line:84%
At the same time,
we had some monks.

00:19:19.630 --> 00:19:24.290 align:middle line:84%
And there was the Order of Sion
that ultimately came to be.

00:19:24.290 --> 00:19:27.220 align:middle line:84%
Let's make some kind of--
draw some kind of line

00:19:27.220 --> 00:19:30.340 align:middle line:84%
between these, and explain
who these monks were.

00:19:30.340 --> 00:19:34.330 align:middle line:84%
And explain the
place they inhabited.

00:19:34.330 --> 00:19:36.660 align:middle line:84%
And how this starts
figuring into the story.

00:19:36.660 --> 00:19:38.840 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Oh, the Order
of Sion was fascinating.

00:19:38.840 --> 00:19:41.410 align:middle line:84%
And I have to give credit to
Baigent, Leigh, and Lincoln.

00:19:41.410 --> 00:19:42.785 align:middle line:10%
Because they really
sort of found

00:19:42.785 --> 00:19:45.409 align:middle line:10%
that out when they were writing
"Holy Blood, Holy Grail," which

00:19:45.409 --> 00:19:47.260 align:middle line:10%
actually helped me a
lot in my understanding

00:19:47.260 --> 00:19:49.897 align:middle line:10%
of bringing all these
confusing things together.

00:19:49.897 --> 00:19:52.480 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out that there was
a group of monks that suddenly

00:19:52.480 --> 00:19:54.230 align:middle line:84%
moved from all the
way from Calabria,

00:19:54.230 --> 00:19:55.840 align:middle line:90%
which is in southern Sicily.

00:19:55.840 --> 00:19:57.970 align:middle line:84%
They've moved all the
way up to Europe--

00:19:57.970 --> 00:19:59.960 align:middle line:90%
not exactly easy back then--

00:19:59.960 --> 00:20:03.280 align:middle line:84%
and they found themselves
in this particular place

00:20:03.280 --> 00:20:07.090 align:middle line:84%
that was run by Canossa
Matilda the Tuscan.

00:20:07.090 --> 00:20:09.372 align:middle line:84%
And basically she gave
them a plot of land.

00:20:09.372 --> 00:20:10.830 align:middle line:84%
And they said,
thank you very much.

00:20:10.830 --> 00:20:13.500 align:middle line:84%
And they built themselves
a nice, little cathedral.

00:20:13.500 --> 00:20:15.640 align:middle line:84%
And then, about 20
years later, they just

00:20:15.640 --> 00:20:18.510 align:middle line:90%
buggered off down to Jerusalem.

00:20:18.510 --> 00:20:21.400 align:middle line:84%
I was like, you just don't just
move halfway across Europe,

00:20:21.400 --> 00:20:23.440 align:middle line:84%
build yourself a big
church, and then leave it,

00:20:23.440 --> 00:20:25.715 align:middle line:84%
and go off 2,000 miles
to play somewhere else.

00:20:25.715 --> 00:20:27.090 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: There's some
motivation, though, behind it.

00:20:27.090 --> 00:20:28.125 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Extraordinary
motivation.

00:20:28.125 --> 00:20:28.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:20:28.500 --> 00:20:29.958 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And it
turns out that they

00:20:29.958 --> 00:20:33.180 align:middle line:84%
were grooming a very young
man, who, in time, would become

00:20:33.180 --> 00:20:36.420 align:middle line:84%
the first patriarch of
Jerusalem, who then, in turn,

00:20:36.420 --> 00:20:41.070 align:middle line:84%
installed the monks in the
rundown basilica on Mount Sion,

00:20:41.070 --> 00:20:43.110 align:middle line:84%
where they became known
as the Order of Sion.

00:20:43.110 --> 00:20:45.318 align:middle line:84%
And they were claiming that
all that they were saying

00:20:45.318 --> 00:20:47.760 align:middle line:84%
was, we have come back to
basically finish a job that

00:20:47.760 --> 00:20:49.819 align:middle line:90%
was begun a long time ago.

00:20:49.819 --> 00:20:51.360 align:middle line:84%
There's a certain
part of a bloodline

00:20:51.360 --> 00:20:52.800 align:middle line:90%
that we're protecting here.

00:20:52.800 --> 00:20:55.750 align:middle line:84%
And a certain tradition
that we're protecting.

00:20:55.750 --> 00:20:57.955 align:middle line:84%
And it's important to bring
that back into play now

00:20:57.955 --> 00:20:59.830 align:middle line:84%
with the things that
are happening in Europe.

00:20:59.830 --> 00:21:02.310 align:middle line:84%
In our time, That
window of opportunity

00:21:02.310 --> 00:21:05.550 align:middle line:84%
that has been missing for
1,000 years because of war,

00:21:05.550 --> 00:21:07.380 align:middle line:84%
religious warfare, and
all of these things

00:21:07.380 --> 00:21:09.570 align:middle line:84%
that have been going on,
this is the best moment

00:21:09.570 --> 00:21:11.520 align:middle line:90%
we've ever had for 1,000 years.

00:21:11.520 --> 00:21:13.290 align:middle line:84%
So it's a very dramatic
moment in history,

00:21:13.290 --> 00:21:16.950 align:middle line:84%
where suddenly this pent-up
frustration of bringing back

00:21:16.950 --> 00:21:20.910 align:middle line:84%
a holy bloodline in Europe to
undermine the Catholic Church

00:21:20.910 --> 00:21:21.900 align:middle line:90%
is now in play.

00:21:21.900 --> 00:21:23.310 align:middle line:84%
And that's when
the Templars also

00:21:23.310 --> 00:21:26.229 align:middle line:84%
show up at the very same
moment in Jerusalem.

00:21:26.229 --> 00:21:28.770 align:middle line:84%
So you have these people sort
of going backwards and forwards

00:21:28.770 --> 00:21:30.276 align:middle line:90%
between the two churches.

00:21:30.276 --> 00:21:31.650 align:middle line:10%
You have the monks
with the Order

00:21:31.650 --> 00:21:33.900 align:middle line:10%
of Sion in their
little rundown basilica

00:21:33.900 --> 00:21:35.730 align:middle line:10%
just outside the
gates of Jerusalem.

00:21:35.730 --> 00:21:38.100 align:middle line:84%
And you have the nucleus of
what will become the Templar

00:21:38.100 --> 00:21:40.260 align:middle line:90%
order in the Holy Sepulcher.

00:21:40.260 --> 00:21:42.070 align:middle line:90%
Talking backwards and forwards.

00:21:42.070 --> 00:21:45.620 align:middle line:84%
And there is actually a deed
that I found that shows that

00:21:45.620 --> 00:21:50.080 align:middle line:84%
the Piieuré of Sion is actually
interacting with Hugues de

00:21:50.080 --> 00:21:51.810 align:middle line:84%
Payens, the leader
of the Templars.

00:21:51.810 --> 00:21:55.530 align:middle line:84%
And saying that good relations
exist between our two orders.

00:21:55.530 --> 00:21:58.422 align:middle line:84%
Now this is at least 10 years
before the Templars have

00:21:58.422 --> 00:21:59.880 align:middle line:84%
been made official,
which shows you

00:21:59.880 --> 00:22:02.220 align:middle line:84%
if they're saying that
there's an organization,

00:22:02.220 --> 00:22:05.550 align:middle line:84%
or a good relationship
between the two orders,

00:22:05.550 --> 00:22:07.260 align:middle line:84%
the Order of Sion
and the Templar Order

00:22:07.260 --> 00:22:10.660 align:middle line:84%
must already have been
existing as early as 1104.

00:22:10.660 --> 00:22:11.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Well, and this says--

00:22:11.970 --> 00:22:13.761 align:middle line:84%
one of the documents
I noticed in your book

00:22:13.761 --> 00:22:16.955 align:middle line:84%
said the Order of Sion--
it was founded in 1090.

00:22:16.955 --> 00:22:17.955 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Quite possibly.

00:22:17.955 --> 00:22:18.913 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Even earlier.

00:22:18.913 --> 00:22:19.770 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yes.

00:22:19.770 --> 00:22:23.640 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So this changes
the historical record

00:22:23.640 --> 00:22:26.650 align:middle line:84%
in terms of when the
Templars even came to be.

00:22:26.650 --> 00:22:28.840 align:middle line:84%
So this was all
mounting long before

00:22:28.840 --> 00:22:31.200 align:middle line:84%
the common historical
records recognize.

00:22:31.200 --> 00:22:32.200 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, absolutely.

00:22:32.200 --> 00:22:34.491 align:middle line:84%
In fact, one of the best
things that my history teacher

00:22:34.491 --> 00:22:35.814 align:middle line:90%
taught me when I was 11.

00:22:35.814 --> 00:22:37.879 align:middle line:84%
The only thing that stayed
in my head in school

00:22:37.879 --> 00:22:39.420 align:middle line:84%
was the fact that
if you want to look

00:22:39.420 --> 00:22:42.240 align:middle line:84%
at the true story behind
anything in history,

00:22:42.240 --> 00:22:43.470 align:middle line:90%
go back 50 years.

00:22:43.470 --> 00:22:45.240 align:middle line:84%
Because that's when
things really begin

00:22:45.240 --> 00:22:47.295 align:middle line:90%
to rise out of the ground.

00:22:47.295 --> 00:22:48.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Let's rise.

00:22:48.170 --> 00:22:49.020 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: The root of things.

00:22:49.020 --> 00:22:49.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, absolutely.

00:22:49.360 --> 00:22:50.360 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And that's
what I basically did.

00:22:50.360 --> 00:22:51.940 align:middle line:84%
I said, how far back
can I take this?

00:22:51.940 --> 00:22:54.860 align:middle line:84%
And yes, you had these
monks that moved suddenly

00:22:54.860 --> 00:22:57.789 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of nowhere, to
the other middle of nowhere,

00:22:57.789 --> 00:23:00.330 align:middle line:84%
to establish a relationship with
a young boy who then becomes

00:23:00.330 --> 00:23:01.560 align:middle line:90%
the patriarch of Jerusalem.

00:23:01.560 --> 00:23:04.030 align:middle line:84%
And In the meantime, you
have all the founding players

00:23:04.030 --> 00:23:06.870 align:middle line:84%
of the Templars making
family connections

00:23:06.870 --> 00:23:07.920 align:middle line:90%
in that part of Europe.

00:23:07.920 --> 00:23:10.740 align:middle line:84%
And making friends with the
monks, or making friends

00:23:10.740 --> 00:23:14.160 align:middle line:84%
with other influential people,
who, them, in 20 years--

00:23:14.160 --> 00:23:16.426 align:middle line:84%
and they were in no hurry
to do this, by the way.

00:23:16.426 --> 00:23:16.760 align:middle line:90%
20 years later--

00:23:16.760 --> 00:23:17.240 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:23:17.240 --> 00:23:17.860 align:middle line:90%
Long-term thinking.

00:23:17.860 --> 00:23:18.040 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:23:18.040 --> 00:23:19.915 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: --the players
suddenly come together

00:23:19.915 --> 00:23:22.000 align:middle line:90%
in a fortuitous moment in time.

00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:25.077 align:middle line:84%
So it's a beautiful plan, but
they were very, very patient.

00:23:25.077 --> 00:23:27.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And there's one
thing, as you just said.

00:23:27.160 --> 00:23:29.910 align:middle line:84%
This kind of an
uninhabitable land almost.

00:23:29.910 --> 00:23:31.920 align:middle line:90%
I mean, rough land.

00:23:31.920 --> 00:23:33.890 align:middle line:84%
Not the prime
picking, so to speak.

00:23:33.890 --> 00:23:36.210 align:middle line:84%
This keeps coming
up again and again

00:23:36.210 --> 00:23:38.550 align:middle line:90%
throughout the Templar story--

00:23:38.550 --> 00:23:41.280 align:middle line:84%
is when they're offered
vast tracts of land,

00:23:41.280 --> 00:23:43.917 align:middle line:84%
that they would often choose
what appeared to be subpar--

00:23:43.917 --> 00:23:44.875 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Very had ones.

00:23:44.875 --> 00:23:46.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: --really bad lands.

00:23:46.280 --> 00:23:47.850 align:middle line:90%
They'd choose the bad lands.

00:23:47.850 --> 00:23:49.890 align:middle line:84%
And again, now let's
go back to Sion.

00:23:49.890 --> 00:23:54.060 align:middle line:84%
Because now we get into the
story of telluric energy.

00:23:54.060 --> 00:23:55.290 align:middle line:90%
Ley lines.

00:23:55.290 --> 00:23:57.240 align:middle line:84%
Energy rising from
certain areas that

00:23:57.240 --> 00:24:00.540 align:middle line:84%
make certain states of
consciousness possible,

00:24:00.540 --> 00:24:04.660 align:middle line:84%
that are desirable to
build certain edifices on.

00:24:04.660 --> 00:24:05.460 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:24:05.460 --> 00:24:07.590 align:middle line:84%
So let's go back to
that-- as you say,

00:24:07.590 --> 00:24:09.700 align:middle line:90%
kind of rundown basilica.

00:24:09.700 --> 00:24:10.500 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:24:10.500 --> 00:24:12.210 align:middle line:84%
It's a very strange
situation, where

00:24:12.210 --> 00:24:14.490 align:middle line:84%
you have the guy that's
now running Jerusalem--

00:24:14.490 --> 00:24:15.530 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, let's
talk about that.

00:24:15.530 --> 00:24:16.740 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Brigands
are running around.

00:24:16.740 --> 00:24:19.470 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of annoyed Arabs
running around, because they've

00:24:19.470 --> 00:24:21.940 align:middle line:90%
just lost their capital.

00:24:21.940 --> 00:24:24.060 align:middle line:84%
So of course, they're
going to try and get it.

00:24:24.060 --> 00:24:25.760 align:middle line:90%
So what does the patriarch do?

00:24:25.760 --> 00:24:26.560 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:24:26.560 --> 00:24:29.130 align:middle line:84%
Instead of living in the really
safe haven inside the walls

00:24:29.130 --> 00:24:31.440 align:middle line:84%
of the city, I'm
going to take refuge

00:24:31.440 --> 00:24:33.820 align:middle line:84%
in a rundown basilica
outside the walls

00:24:33.820 --> 00:24:35.900 align:middle line:84%
to the place where we
can be basically killed.

00:24:35.900 --> 00:24:36.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:24:36.700 --> 00:24:38.260 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It doesn't
make any sense.

00:24:38.260 --> 00:24:40.593 align:middle line:84%
And of course, you go back
in history and you find out--

00:24:40.593 --> 00:24:42.600 align:middle line:84%
and we're now talking
thousands of years--

00:24:42.600 --> 00:24:46.320 align:middle line:84%
of the continuous
creation of temples,

00:24:46.320 --> 00:24:49.290 align:middle line:84%
and sacred buildings
in specific hot spots.

00:24:49.290 --> 00:24:52.800 align:middle line:84%
And we now know today, by
matching myth, tradition,

00:24:52.800 --> 00:24:55.770 align:middle line:84%
and technology, that all of
these ancient sacred sites

00:24:55.770 --> 00:24:58.920 align:middle line:84%
are all built on the earth's
electromagnetic pathways.

00:24:58.920 --> 00:25:00.660 align:middle line:84%
Specifically the
junction points.

00:25:00.660 --> 00:25:03.690 align:middle line:84%
What we call node points,
or even navels of the Earth,

00:25:03.690 --> 00:25:05.220 align:middle line:90%
if you want to go that far.

00:25:05.220 --> 00:25:06.870 align:middle line:84%
And these hot spots
have the ability

00:25:06.870 --> 00:25:08.910 align:middle line:90%
to alter human consciousness.

00:25:08.910 --> 00:25:10.960 align:middle line:90%
This is now a proven fact.

00:25:10.960 --> 00:25:13.140 align:middle line:84%
We can even measure the
energy that we don't feel,

00:25:13.140 --> 00:25:13.996 align:middle line:90%
that we can see.

00:25:13.996 --> 00:25:15.370 align:middle line:84%
And this is why
these places were

00:25:15.370 --> 00:25:17.590 align:middle line:84%
very important to
this group of people.

00:25:17.590 --> 00:25:19.830 align:middle line:84%
Because when you follow
the Templars story, even

00:25:19.830 --> 00:25:22.080 align:middle line:84%
the Cistercian story,
the other group

00:25:22.080 --> 00:25:24.930 align:middle line:84%
that were fundamentally
behind the Templars,

00:25:24.930 --> 00:25:26.945 align:middle line:84%
they always chose these
very unusual locations.

00:25:26.945 --> 00:25:28.320 align:middle line:84%
And when you go
and look at where

00:25:28.320 --> 00:25:30.570 align:middle line:84%
they built their
buildings, yes, there

00:25:30.570 --> 00:25:32.950 align:middle line:84%
is something very
telluric about them.

00:25:32.950 --> 00:25:34.650 align:middle line:84%
There's a different
feel about them.

00:25:34.650 --> 00:25:37.320 align:middle line:84%
And that's what was part of
this spiritual technology

00:25:37.320 --> 00:25:39.449 align:middle line:84%
that they were
trying to rediscover.

00:25:39.449 --> 00:25:40.740 align:middle line:90%
They weren't looking for money.

00:25:40.740 --> 00:25:43.140 align:middle line:84%
They were looking for a
spiritual treasure, something

00:25:43.140 --> 00:25:46.160 align:middle line:84%
that would help them overcome
the problems of the period,

00:25:46.160 --> 00:25:47.520 align:middle line:90%
which of course is barbarity.

00:25:47.520 --> 00:25:50.100 align:middle line:84%
They wanted to-- they
can rise up the spirits

00:25:50.100 --> 00:25:51.730 align:middle line:90%
to come forward again.

00:25:51.730 --> 00:25:54.810 align:middle line:84%
So they would choose really
inhospitable places that

00:25:54.810 --> 00:25:59.070 align:middle line:84%
used to be temple places,
or sacred places that had

00:25:59.070 --> 00:26:00.780 align:middle line:90%
been run down because of war.

00:26:00.780 --> 00:26:02.520 align:middle line:84%
So it starts to
make sense when you

00:26:02.520 --> 00:26:05.012 align:middle line:84%
start seeing the picture from
the bigger point of view.

00:26:05.012 --> 00:26:06.720 align:middle line:84%
And why they went
through so much trouble

00:26:06.720 --> 00:26:08.520 align:middle line:84%
to find places that,
frankly, I wouldn't

00:26:08.520 --> 00:26:09.940 align:middle line:90%
give $0.05 for this building.

00:26:09.940 --> 00:26:10.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:26:10.310 --> 00:26:11.272 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: But I
want that building.

00:26:11.272 --> 00:26:11.354 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:26:11.354 --> 00:26:11.600 align:middle line:90%
Because it worked.

00:26:11.600 --> 00:26:13.660 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And some of them
had not been developed before.

00:26:13.660 --> 00:26:14.490 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:26:14.490 --> 00:26:16.320 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And yet
they understood

00:26:16.320 --> 00:26:18.480 align:middle line:84%
the nature of what the
land itself was about.

00:26:18.480 --> 00:26:20.890 align:middle line:84%
Although to the outside
world it would look like,

00:26:20.890 --> 00:26:22.992 align:middle line:90%
oh, these humble ascetics.

00:26:22.992 --> 00:26:24.450 align:middle line:84%
They'll eschew the
palace they were

00:26:24.450 --> 00:26:27.550 align:middle line:84%
given for this badlands
track of dirt over here.

00:26:27.550 --> 00:26:28.350 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: I know.

00:26:28.350 --> 00:26:30.545 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And in fact, that
was just a public perception.

00:26:30.545 --> 00:26:30.970 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:26:30.970 --> 00:26:32.265 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't just out of humility.

00:26:32.265 --> 00:26:33.700 align:middle line:84%
It's they knew
what was going on.

00:26:33.700 --> 00:26:34.500 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: I know.

00:26:34.500 --> 00:26:36.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And yet, no
one else did around them.

00:26:36.420 --> 00:26:37.230 align:middle line:90%
Not the Royalty.

00:26:37.230 --> 00:26:38.030 align:middle line:90%
Not the church.

00:26:38.030 --> 00:26:40.150 align:middle line:84%
No one around them
knew what was going on.

00:26:40.150 --> 00:26:41.653 align:middle line:84%
They didn't possess
that knowledge.

00:26:41.653 --> 00:26:42.520 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I mean,
they were humble,

00:26:42.520 --> 00:26:44.230 align:middle line:90%
but they also went beyond that.

00:26:44.230 --> 00:26:44.530 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's exactly--

00:26:44.530 --> 00:26:46.480 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Given the choice
between having a bed of straw,

00:26:46.480 --> 00:26:48.210 align:middle line:84%
now they will live in a hovel
underneath the staircase.

00:26:48.210 --> 00:26:48.570 align:middle line:90%
You know.

00:26:48.570 --> 00:26:50.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're going to
talk about those characters

00:26:50.190 --> 00:26:50.730 align:middle line:90%
in a minute.

00:26:50.730 --> 00:26:51.610 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:26:51.610 --> 00:26:52.410 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:26:52.410 --> 00:26:56.670 align:middle line:84%
And the interesting thing
was that particular abbey--

00:26:56.670 --> 00:26:59.460 align:middle line:84%
and we're going to find this
out throughout the story--

00:26:59.460 --> 00:27:01.830 align:middle line:84%
the great days where
documents were signed,

00:27:01.830 --> 00:27:06.330 align:middle line:84%
or campaigns were begun,
often, or many times,

00:27:06.330 --> 00:27:09.870 align:middle line:84%
were in honor of the feast day
of either John the Baptist,

00:27:09.870 --> 00:27:11.370 align:middle line:90%
or Mary Magdalene.

00:27:11.370 --> 00:27:16.080 align:middle line:84%
So all of it seemed to hook
back into a period 1,000 years

00:27:16.080 --> 00:27:17.550 align:middle line:90%
earlier, and the bloodline?

00:27:17.550 --> 00:27:17.800 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:27:17.800 --> 00:27:18.420 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:27:18.420 --> 00:27:20.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that abbey was
dedicated to John the Baptist,

00:27:20.910 --> 00:27:21.710 align:middle line:90%
as I recall.

00:27:21.710 --> 00:27:22.870 align:middle line:90%
Is that correct?

00:27:22.870 --> 00:27:23.580 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: The one in Mount Sion?

00:27:23.580 --> 00:27:24.440 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:27:24.440 --> 00:27:25.464 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: To Mary.

00:27:25.464 --> 00:27:26.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, that was Mary.

00:27:26.630 --> 00:27:27.060 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:27:27.060 --> 00:27:27.450 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:27:27.450 --> 00:27:28.005 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:27:28.005 --> 00:27:28.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And let's
talk about that.

00:27:28.410 --> 00:27:30.900 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: The other one
was actually-- yeah.

00:27:30.900 --> 00:27:36.120 align:middle line:84%
There was a place also where
the Knights of St. John

00:27:36.120 --> 00:27:38.910 align:middle line:84%
were in Jerusalem, which you'd
think has to do with John

00:27:38.910 --> 00:27:39.760 align:middle line:90%
the Baptist.

00:27:39.760 --> 00:27:40.676 align:middle line:90%
But actually it's not.

00:27:40.676 --> 00:27:43.350 align:middle line:84%
It's to do with St. John
[INAUDIBLE] of Cyprus,

00:27:43.350 --> 00:27:45.470 align:middle line:84%
who also gave up his
wealth to become--

00:27:45.470 --> 00:27:45.665 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, right.

00:27:45.665 --> 00:27:45.730 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:27:45.730 --> 00:27:47.270 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Poorer of spirit.

00:27:47.270 --> 00:27:48.580 align:middle line:90%
I mean poor of pocket.

00:27:48.580 --> 00:27:51.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's
go back to Our Lady.

00:27:51.120 --> 00:27:53.980 align:middle line:84%
Chapels being dedicated
all over to Our Lady.

00:27:53.980 --> 00:27:54.780 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:27:54.780 --> 00:27:55.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:27:55.580 --> 00:27:56.880 align:middle line:90%
And again, the bloodline.

00:27:56.880 --> 00:28:01.680 align:middle line:84%
And how these people that
gathered at that rundown abbey

00:28:01.680 --> 00:28:02.880 align:middle line:90%
were affiliated with that.

00:28:02.880 --> 00:28:03.150 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:28:03.150 --> 00:28:04.320 align:middle line:84%
I'm surprised that
no-one's picked up

00:28:04.320 --> 00:28:06.570 align:middle line:84%
on this, even a lot of
the Templar historians.

00:28:06.570 --> 00:28:09.210 align:middle line:84%
Because everybody
equates the Templars

00:28:09.210 --> 00:28:10.740 align:middle line:90%
with the Catholic Church.

00:28:10.740 --> 00:28:14.110 align:middle line:84%
But they never dedicated any
of their buildings to Jesus.

00:28:14.110 --> 00:28:14.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:28:14.910 --> 00:28:15.690 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Doesn't that
sort a little bit odd?

00:28:15.690 --> 00:28:16.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's what
I found interesting.

00:28:16.560 --> 00:28:18.768 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Alarm bells should
be ringing at this point.

00:28:18.768 --> 00:28:19.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:28:19.590 --> 00:28:22.602 align:middle line:10%
>>SILVA: For example, in
Portugal, where the Templars--

00:28:22.602 --> 00:28:24.060 align:middle line:10%
we'll talk about
this in a second--

00:28:24.060 --> 00:28:25.950 align:middle line:10%
where they created the
country, every single thing

00:28:25.950 --> 00:28:28.090 align:middle line:10%
that they built was dedicated
to Mary Magdalene and John

00:28:28.090 --> 00:28:28.580 align:middle line:10%
the Baptist.

00:28:28.580 --> 00:28:28.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:28:28.950 --> 00:28:31.320 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Setting up all
of their civil calendars

00:28:31.320 --> 00:28:33.510 align:middle line:90%
on the feast day of either.

00:28:33.510 --> 00:28:36.660 align:middle line:84%
There's something that
should be looked at here.

00:28:36.660 --> 00:28:38.070 align:middle line:90%
And it was the same thing--

00:28:38.070 --> 00:28:40.980 align:middle line:84%
whether it was in Jerusalem,
in France, and in Portugal,

00:28:40.980 --> 00:28:43.530 align:middle line:84%
they were always
following this connection.

00:28:43.530 --> 00:28:45.429 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out
that when you start

00:28:45.429 --> 00:28:47.970 align:middle line:84%
looking at the lineage going
all the way back, that they were

00:28:47.970 --> 00:28:50.520 align:middle line:90%
protecting a certain bloodline.

00:28:50.520 --> 00:28:52.170 align:middle line:84%
And this is one of
the things that I

00:28:52.170 --> 00:28:54.600 align:middle line:90%
was amazed during my research.

00:28:54.600 --> 00:28:56.670 align:middle line:90%
I came across this--

00:28:56.670 --> 00:28:59.040 align:middle line:84%
actually, it was a
massive, massive book.

00:28:59.040 --> 00:29:00.570 align:middle line:90%
It was so big.

00:29:00.570 --> 00:29:01.460 align:middle line:90%
About that thick.

00:29:01.460 --> 00:29:03.180 align:middle line:90%
No index, of course.

00:29:03.180 --> 00:29:05.130 align:middle line:84%
So I wasn't quite sure
what I was looking for.

00:29:05.130 --> 00:29:08.850 align:middle line:84%
But somewhere on page 680
there is a swearing-in ceremony

00:29:08.850 --> 00:29:11.250 align:middle line:84%
of the grand master of
the Templars in Portugal

00:29:11.250 --> 00:29:13.930 align:middle line:84%
that declares to protect
the bloodline of David.

00:29:13.930 --> 00:29:16.200 align:middle line:84%
Now, you're not going to
put that in the swearing-in

00:29:16.200 --> 00:29:19.080 align:middle line:84%
ceremony unless they're
there to protect a bloodline.

00:29:19.080 --> 00:29:22.170 align:middle line:84%
So one of the central
themes of the Order of Sion,

00:29:22.170 --> 00:29:24.120 align:middle line:90%
who basically the people that--

00:29:24.120 --> 00:29:26.100 align:middle line:84%
I won't say bankrolled
the Templars,

00:29:26.100 --> 00:29:27.620 align:middle line:84%
but they were
certainly fundamental

00:29:27.620 --> 00:29:29.490 align:middle line:84%
in creating the
original Templars.

00:29:29.490 --> 00:29:31.290 align:middle line:84%
And most of the
Templars, apparently,

00:29:31.290 --> 00:29:33.330 align:middle line:84%
were also members of
the Order of Sion.

00:29:33.330 --> 00:29:35.520 align:middle line:10%
And that was revealed
in secret dossiers

00:29:35.520 --> 00:29:40.220 align:middle line:10%
that were found by Henry
Lincoln and company in Paris.

00:29:40.220 --> 00:29:43.500 align:middle line:10%
And that these documents that
were put there deliberately

00:29:43.500 --> 00:29:46.590 align:middle line:10%
showed that the Templars
and the Order of Sion

00:29:46.590 --> 00:29:48.030 align:middle line:10%
basically were the same people.

00:29:48.030 --> 00:29:51.460 align:middle line:84%
Or that the two organizations
were so intertwined.

00:29:51.460 --> 00:29:54.240 align:middle line:84%
And the Order of Sion's
declared aim was always

00:29:54.240 --> 00:29:58.260 align:middle line:84%
that we are here to resuscitate
the bloodline of David.

00:29:58.260 --> 00:30:01.350 align:middle line:84%
And also the bloodline that
was split from the Sumerian

00:30:01.350 --> 00:30:03.150 align:middle line:84%
culture, through the
Egyptian culture,

00:30:03.150 --> 00:30:05.520 align:middle line:84%
and eventually find its
way into central Europe.

00:30:05.520 --> 00:30:09.480 align:middle line:84%
This is the rightful bloodline
of the divine kings and queens,

00:30:09.480 --> 00:30:11.730 align:middle line:84%
who were leading people
up from the ground.

00:30:11.730 --> 00:30:14.410 align:middle line:84%
To give them a ladder
up in the state of life,

00:30:14.410 --> 00:30:16.680 align:middle line:84%
which is what the Catholic
Church wasn't doing.

00:30:16.680 --> 00:30:18.960 align:middle line:84%
Because they supported
the Carolingians.

00:30:18.960 --> 00:30:21.640 align:middle line:84%
And the Carolingians,
essentially

00:30:21.640 --> 00:30:24.300 align:middle line:84%
had a big coup in
the middle of Europe.

00:30:24.300 --> 00:30:26.550 align:middle line:84%
They had basically run down
the Merovingian bloodline,

00:30:26.550 --> 00:30:28.050 align:middle line:90%
and drove it underground.

00:30:28.050 --> 00:30:29.550 align:middle line:84%
Because they held
the biggest secret

00:30:29.550 --> 00:30:32.460 align:middle line:84%
of all, which was the true
story of what was happening

00:30:32.460 --> 00:30:34.830 align:middle line:84%
with the true Christian
brotherhood of Jesus,

00:30:34.830 --> 00:30:36.840 align:middle line:84%
Mary Magdalene, the fact
that they were married,

00:30:36.840 --> 00:30:39.048 align:middle line:84%
the fact that there's a
family relationship with John

00:30:39.048 --> 00:30:41.450 align:middle line:84%
the Baptist, which to this
day the church has denied.

