a personal spirituality.

00:33:00.662 --> 00:33:03.120 align:middle line:84%
And it was part of a ritual
called the raising of the dead,

00:33:03.120 --> 00:33:05.370 align:middle line:84%
or the living resurrection
as they called it.

00:33:05.370 --> 00:33:07.980 align:middle line:84%
And so the women wore
the red robe of office,

00:33:07.980 --> 00:33:11.400 align:middle line:84%
called "ritus," which is what
we get the word "rituals" from.

00:33:11.400 --> 00:33:12.930 align:middle line:90%
And it was a red robe.

00:33:12.930 --> 00:33:15.480 align:middle line:84%
So that's where the concept
of the woman in red comes in.

00:33:15.480 --> 00:33:18.225 align:middle line:84%
So fast forward 3,000 years
late with Mary Magdalene,

00:33:18.225 --> 00:33:21.480 align:middle line:84%
with the woman wearing the
red robe, what happens to her?

00:33:21.480 --> 00:33:23.430 align:middle line:84%
She gets basically
mislabeled as a prostitute.

00:33:23.430 --> 00:33:23.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:33:23.790 --> 00:33:25.530 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Since then, we've been
having a problem with women

00:33:25.530 --> 00:33:26.430 align:middle line:90%
wearing the color red.

00:33:26.430 --> 00:33:26.835 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:33:26.835 --> 00:33:26.970 align:middle line:90%
Jezebel.

00:33:26.970 --> 00:33:27.240 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:33:27.240 --> 00:33:29.370 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So the whole thing
