>>REGINA: Shocked
down to my tootsies.

00:38:06.040 --> 00:38:07.819 align:middle line:90%
Like what is going on here?

00:38:07.819 --> 00:38:09.610 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I know exactly
what you're saying.

00:38:09.610 --> 00:38:10.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:38:10.120 --> 00:38:10.590 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:38:10.590 --> 00:38:12.506 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: This is why
these places were chosen.

00:38:12.506 --> 00:38:13.590 align:middle line:90%
They're just not a cave.

00:38:13.590 --> 00:38:16.139 align:middle line:84%
It's a specific place
on the mountain where

00:38:16.139 --> 00:38:18.180 align:middle line:84%
the laws of physics are
slightly different to get

00:38:18.180 --> 00:38:19.672 align:middle line:90%
you to have that experience.

00:38:19.672 --> 00:38:21.630 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I just sat down
and it was happening.

00:38:21.630 --> 00:38:24.120 align:middle line:90%
It's so prominent in that area.

00:38:24.120 --> 00:38:26.280 align:middle line:84%
Again, opening into
these other periods,

00:38:26.280 --> 00:38:27.620 align:middle line:90%
and these other energies.

00:38:27.620 --> 00:38:28.420 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:38:28.420 --> 00:38:30.210 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I think he's the most
important person in the Bible,

00:38:30.210 --> 00:38:31.276 align:middle line:90%
actually.

00:38:31.276 --> 00:38:33.150 align:middle line:84%
And so little time--
it's funny how so little

00:38:33.150 --> 00:38:34.680 align:middle line:90%
is devoted to this guy.

00:38:34.680 --> 00:38:36.612 align:middle line:84%
And yet, he's so
huge, so prominent,

00:38:36.612 --> 00:38:38.070 align:middle line:84%
in the whole, big
scheme of things.

00:38:38.070 --> 00:38:40.680 align:middle line:84%
And all the peoples
around the era

00:38:40.680 --> 00:38:42.356 align:middle line:84%
of the time of the
gnostic Christians--

00:38:42.356 --> 00:38:44.980 align:middle line:84%
which is what I was also part of
the understanding of the book,

00:38:44.980 --> 00:38:47.430 align:middle line:84%
which was why were the gnostic
Christians being killed

00:38:47.430 --> 00:38:48.300 align:middle line:90%
by the Catholics.

00:38:48.300 --> 00:38:49.770 align:middle line:84%
Although fundamentalist
Christians

00:38:49.770 --> 00:38:52.290 align:middle line:84%
that there were at the time
didn't make any sense, well,

00:38:52.290 --> 00:38:55.104 align:middle line:84%
the gnostic Christians, and all
the other sects of the period,

00:38:55.104 --> 00:38:56.520 align:middle line:84%
all believed that
John the Baptist

00:38:56.520 --> 00:38:59.070 align:middle line:90%
was the man to go look at that.

00:38:59.070 --> 00:39:00.720 align:middle line:84%
He's following a
very old tradition.

00:39:00.720 --> 00:39:04.740 align:middle line:84%
In fact, his name,
Johannes, goes all the way,

00:39:04.740 --> 00:39:07.020 align:middle line:84%
etymologically, back
to Oannes, who is one

00:39:07.020 --> 00:39:08.820 align:middle line:90%
of the created gods of Sumeria.

00:39:08.820 --> 00:39:11.280 align:middle line:84%
The fish man-- half
man, half fish.

00:39:11.280 --> 00:39:12.750 align:middle line:84%
And what were they
interested in?

00:39:12.750 --> 00:39:15.280 align:middle line:84%
The first portion of
your initiation ceremony

00:39:15.280 --> 00:39:18.900 align:middle line:84%
is ritual baptism through a
very special type of water.

00:39:18.900 --> 00:39:21.000 align:middle line:84%
There's something
potent about this water.

00:39:21.000 --> 00:39:23.250 align:middle line:84%
And where John the Baptist
did his ceremonies was

00:39:23.250 --> 00:39:25.160 align:middle line:84%
in a place called the
place of crossing,

00:39:25.160 --> 00:39:27.060 align:middle line:84%
where there is four
rivers across--

00:39:27.060 --> 00:39:28.830 align:middle line:90%
on this sacred mount--

00:39:28.830 --> 00:39:31.440 align:middle line:84%
and where the telluric
lines of the Earth

00:39:31.440 --> 00:39:33.830 align:middle line:90%
also are granted to that water.

00:39:33.830 --> 00:39:36.030 align:middle line:84%
That's something that
NASA discovered recently--

00:39:36.030 --> 00:39:37.904 align:middle line:84%
that the Earth's magnetic
lines are attracted

00:39:37.904 --> 00:39:40.110 align:middle line:84%
to certain parts
of the world where

00:39:40.110 --> 00:39:42.760 align:middle line:84%
a specific type of water--
a very clear and clean type

00:39:42.760 --> 00:39:44.010 align:middle line:90%
of water-- exists.

00:39:44.010 --> 00:39:46.350 align:middle line:84%
So it builds up this
numinous energy,

00:39:46.350 --> 00:39:49.170 align:middle line:84%
which then develops a numinous
state of quality within you.

00:39:49.170 --> 00:39:51.039 align:middle line:84%
So he was following
a very old tradition

00:39:51.039 --> 00:39:53.580 align:middle line:84%
of manipulation of energy, you
know, for a spiritual purpose.

00:39:53.580 --> 00:39:53.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:39:53.910 --> 00:39:54.935 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:39:54.935 --> 00:39:56.810 align:middle line:84%
That still exists to
this day, I would argue.

00:39:56.810 --> 00:39:58.360 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: I find it fascinating.

00:39:58.360 --> 00:39:59.160 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:39:59.160 --> 00:40:01.980 align:middle line:84%
Now we're going to hop
through a little bit

00:40:01.980 --> 00:40:06.780 align:middle line:84%
of the history of the region,
and the Moors who had invaded.

00:40:06.780 --> 00:40:09.810 align:middle line:84%
And essentially, the
living conditions.

00:40:09.810 --> 00:40:12.960 align:middle line:84%
And then the rag-tag
assembly of people

00:40:12.960 --> 00:40:14.640 align:middle line:90%
that became the "crusade."

00:40:14.640 --> 00:40:16.065 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, my God.

00:40:16.065 --> 00:40:19.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so, we talk
about poor, ignorant.

00:40:19.980 --> 00:40:22.140 align:middle line:90%
Talk about bloody.

00:40:22.140 --> 00:40:25.630 align:middle line:84%
So I would like you to launch
into the Palestinian story.

00:40:25.630 --> 00:40:30.570 align:middle line:84%
First of all, the Arabs
invaded Palestine.

00:40:30.570 --> 00:40:32.184 align:middle line:84%
It sounds like in
the seventh century.

00:40:32.184 --> 00:40:33.600 align:middle line:84%
So you take it
forward from there,

00:40:33.600 --> 00:40:35.790 align:middle line:84%
and set the stage for
what was going on.

00:40:35.790 --> 00:40:38.370 align:middle line:84%
All these people
from Portugal over

00:40:38.370 --> 00:40:41.430 align:middle line:84%
were basically on the
defensive the whole time,

00:40:41.430 --> 00:40:44.970 align:middle line:84%
because the Arabs had made
such incredible progress

00:40:44.970 --> 00:40:47.220 align:middle line:90%
into their lands.

00:40:47.220 --> 00:40:48.180 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:40:48.180 --> 00:40:50.430 align:middle line:84%
And then it got more complicated
because the Arabs are

00:40:50.430 --> 00:40:51.597 align:middle line:90%
fighting amongst themselves.

00:40:51.597 --> 00:40:53.680 align:middle line:84%
I believe there was just
this mass-- it was almost

00:40:53.680 --> 00:40:54.830 align:middle line:90%
like a Monty Python thing.

00:40:54.830 --> 00:40:55.090 align:middle line:90%
It's so funny.

00:40:55.090 --> 00:40:57.436 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Just give us a
massive movement of Arabs,

00:40:57.436 --> 00:40:58.560 align:middle line:90%
and where they had come in.

00:40:58.560 --> 00:41:01.350 align:middle line:84%
Starting in the seventh
century, or even before,

00:41:01.350 --> 00:41:04.515 align:middle line:84%
what their movement
basically resulted in,

00:41:04.515 --> 00:41:06.980 align:middle line:84%
in terms of the takeover
of certain lands and such.

00:41:06.980 --> 00:41:07.330 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:41:07.330 --> 00:41:09.371 align:middle line:84%
They began to basically
fight amongst themselves.

00:41:09.371 --> 00:41:14.580 align:middle line:84%
And eventually the Sljuq
Turks became the top dogs

00:41:14.580 --> 00:41:15.560 align:middle line:90%
in the situation.

00:41:15.560 --> 00:41:17.344 align:middle line:84%
And they were
particularly barbaric.

00:41:17.344 --> 00:41:18.760 align:middle line:84%
I mean, these were
barbaric times,

00:41:18.760 --> 00:41:21.630 align:middle line:84%
but they were
particularly barbaric.

00:41:21.630 --> 00:41:23.869 align:middle line:84%
So I had to edit a
lot of the stuff out.

00:41:23.869 --> 00:41:25.660 align:middle line:84%
And so you had this
sort of fighting that--

00:41:25.660 --> 00:41:28.440 align:middle line:84%
this tide that goes in and
out between different factions

00:41:28.440 --> 00:41:29.760 align:middle line:90%
of people.

00:41:29.760 --> 00:41:32.850 align:middle line:84%
Especially around the Balkans,
and around Constantinople,

00:41:32.850 --> 00:41:36.390 align:middle line:84%
where the actual territory
is always shifting hands,

00:41:36.390 --> 00:41:38.920 align:middle line:84%
accordingly, from one
decade to the other.

00:41:38.920 --> 00:41:40.410 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes even less.

00:41:40.410 --> 00:41:42.390 align:middle line:84%
You'd be getting invaded
by different armies

00:41:42.390 --> 00:41:44.681 align:middle line:84%
of different people with
different beliefs almost every

00:41:44.681 --> 00:41:45.630 align:middle line:90%
other week.

00:41:45.630 --> 00:41:47.250 align:middle line:90%
It became so confusing.

00:41:47.250 --> 00:41:51.990 align:middle line:84%
So after a while, what happened
was that the Sljuq Turks really

00:41:51.990 --> 00:41:54.960 align:middle line:84%
sort of took over
the Palestinian area,

00:41:54.960 --> 00:41:56.160 align:middle line:90%
and grounded themselves.

00:41:56.160 --> 00:41:58.980 align:middle line:84%
And became like a bulwark
against any other kind

00:41:58.980 --> 00:42:00.010 align:middle line:90%
of religion.

00:42:00.010 --> 00:42:01.470 align:middle line:84%
And so there's a
lot of frustration

00:42:01.470 --> 00:42:02.970 align:middle line:84%
between all the
Christians in Europe

00:42:02.970 --> 00:42:06.480 align:middle line:84%
who were-- depending on who
was in charge in Jerusalem,

00:42:06.480 --> 00:42:09.900 align:middle line:84%
there would often be given safe
passage to the holy places.

00:42:09.900 --> 00:42:12.761 align:middle line:84%
But when the Turks took over it
was like, no, no, no, no, no.

00:42:12.761 --> 00:42:14.760 align:middle line:84%
Unless you pay us a lot
of money, a lot of gold,

00:42:14.760 --> 00:42:16.160 align:middle line:84%
we're basically
going to gut you.

00:42:16.160 --> 00:42:16.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:42:16.840 --> 00:42:17.680 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And there was
all the gutting going on--

00:42:17.680 --> 00:42:18.513 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Literally.

00:42:18.513 --> 00:42:21.360 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: --literally gutting
going on, on both sides

00:42:21.360 --> 00:42:24.130 align:middle line:84%
of the fence, to
the point where if--

00:42:24.130 --> 00:42:26.610 align:middle line:84%
any pilgrim that was
caught in the wrong time

00:42:26.610 --> 00:42:29.140 align:middle line:84%
at the wrong place
they'd be captured.

00:42:29.140 --> 00:42:30.846 align:middle line:90%
They were put in a square.

00:42:30.846 --> 00:42:32.220 align:middle line:84%
And that the ones
that didn't die

00:42:32.220 --> 00:42:34.110 align:middle line:84%
from exhaustion,
and from beatings,

00:42:34.110 --> 00:42:36.400 align:middle line:84%
they were used for
target practice.

00:42:36.400 --> 00:42:37.560 align:middle line:90%
Live target practice.

00:42:37.560 --> 00:42:40.020 align:middle line:84%
And after that
there were tortured.

00:42:40.020 --> 00:42:41.520 align:middle line:84%
In the meantime,
you had the priests

00:42:41.520 --> 00:42:42.770 align:middle line:90%
egging on all the Christians--

00:42:42.770 --> 00:42:44.364 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, that part.

00:42:44.364 --> 00:42:50.340 align:middle line:84%
Just like in this religious
order, egging the peasant

00:42:50.340 --> 00:42:54.090 align:middle line:84%
soldiers on by telling
them that the Arabs would

00:42:54.090 --> 00:42:55.680 align:middle line:90%
swallow their riches--

00:42:55.680 --> 00:42:57.490 align:middle line:84%
their coins and
their jewels, right?

00:42:57.490 --> 00:42:57.720 align:middle line:90%
So they'd have to cut them open.

00:42:57.720 --> 00:42:59.440 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So they'd have to
cut them in their bellies,

00:42:59.440 --> 00:43:00.330 align:middle line:90%
and probe in the entrail--

00:43:00.330 --> 00:43:01.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: A good way
to motivate them.

00:43:01.070 --> 00:43:03.450 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: --to find out where
these riches were buried.

00:43:03.450 --> 00:43:05.610 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the image
is so horrific.

00:43:05.610 --> 00:43:07.240 align:middle line:84%
And it was happening
on both sides.

00:43:07.240 --> 00:43:08.730 align:middle line:90%
Everybody had lost the plot.

00:43:08.730 --> 00:43:10.650 align:middle line:84%
They were basically
looking after something

00:43:10.650 --> 00:43:11.946 align:middle line:90%
that was no longer spiritual.

00:43:11.946 --> 00:43:13.320 align:middle line:84%
They were looking
after something

00:43:13.320 --> 00:43:14.826 align:middle line:90%
that was now material.

00:43:14.826 --> 00:43:16.200 align:middle line:84%
It was all about
material wealth.

00:43:16.200 --> 00:43:18.570 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of like the Aztecs,
who also lost the plot.

00:43:18.570 --> 00:43:21.070 align:middle line:84%
And the Maya kept the plot,
because they saw the--

00:43:21.070 --> 00:43:21.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh,
distinctly different.

00:43:21.900 --> 00:43:22.180 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:43:22.180 --> 00:43:23.860 align:middle line:84%
They saw the whole
thing as a metaphor.

00:43:23.860 --> 00:43:24.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:43:24.290 --> 00:43:25.560 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: You don't
take this literally.

00:43:25.560 --> 00:43:26.710 align:middle line:90%
It's a metaphor.

00:43:26.710 --> 00:43:29.470 align:middle line:84%
They're tools to aid your
spiritual development.

00:43:29.470 --> 00:43:30.270 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:43:30.270 --> 00:43:32.728 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And that's where Europe
also got it wrong as well.

00:43:32.728 --> 00:43:34.424 align:middle line:84%
Ironically, around
the same time period.

00:43:34.424 --> 00:43:35.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:43:35.340 --> 00:43:36.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yes.

00:43:36.140 --> 00:43:40.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, now as the
incursion of the Moors or Arabs

00:43:40.890 --> 00:43:43.170 align:middle line:84%
occurred in Jerusalem--
as I understand it

00:43:43.170 --> 00:43:47.130 align:middle line:84%
from your book, the only
area that was not taken over

00:43:47.130 --> 00:43:49.680 align:middle line:84%
was the Christian
sector, which was

00:43:49.680 --> 00:43:51.560 align:middle line:84%
where the Church of
the Holy Sepulcher is.

00:43:51.560 --> 00:43:54.900 align:middle line:84%
Which, to this day, is still
in the Christian quadrant

00:43:54.900 --> 00:43:55.710 align:middle line:90%
of Jerusalem.

00:43:55.710 --> 00:43:56.170 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:43:56.170 --> 00:43:56.970 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:43:56.970 --> 00:43:58.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so
how did that remain

00:43:58.560 --> 00:44:00.990 align:middle line:90%
protected amidst all of this?

00:44:00.990 --> 00:44:02.670 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: A lot of the
people who began--

00:44:02.670 --> 00:44:06.190 align:middle line:84%
again, it depends on which
decade you're talking about

00:44:06.190 --> 00:44:08.010 align:middle line:90%
and who is in power.

00:44:08.010 --> 00:44:10.290 align:middle line:84%
But it seems to me, from
the surviving documents,

00:44:10.290 --> 00:44:13.870 align:middle line:84%
that a lot of the Arab
people who were actually

00:44:13.870 --> 00:44:17.180 align:middle line:84%
in control of the whole of the
Palestinian and Jerusalem area,

00:44:17.180 --> 00:44:18.730 align:middle line:84%
they was actually
very enlightened.

00:44:18.730 --> 00:44:21.063 align:middle line:84%
And they recognized that the
only way this problem would

00:44:21.063 --> 00:44:23.410 align:middle line:84%
ever solve itself,
because the location is

00:44:23.410 --> 00:44:25.750 align:middle line:84%
so important to so
many different people,

00:44:25.750 --> 00:44:27.280 align:middle line:90%
is to give access to everyone.

00:44:27.280 --> 00:44:28.480 align:middle line:90%
Everyone is equal.

00:44:28.480 --> 00:44:30.976 align:middle line:84%
But once in a while
the story changes.

00:44:30.976 --> 00:44:32.350 align:middle line:84%
Because you got
someone else that

00:44:32.350 --> 00:44:34.572 align:middle line:84%
comes in, and has lost
the plot, and they

00:44:34.572 --> 00:44:36.280 align:middle line:84%
want to basically
control the whole thing

00:44:36.280 --> 00:44:37.800 align:middle line:90%
for their own political aims.

00:44:37.800 --> 00:44:38.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:44:38.150 --> 00:44:39.100 align:middle line:90%
And this is interesting.

00:44:39.100 --> 00:44:40.850 align:middle line:84%
Again, this is where
the story is nuanced.

00:44:40.850 --> 00:44:43.390 align:middle line:84%
Because, again,
within Arabic culture

00:44:43.390 --> 00:44:47.500 align:middle line:84%
was a very high understanding of
some of the spiritual teachings

00:44:47.500 --> 00:44:48.580 align:middle line:90%
you're talking about.

00:44:48.580 --> 00:44:52.420 align:middle line:84%
Mathematics, geometry,
sound, music.

00:44:52.420 --> 00:44:55.360 align:middle line:84%
And they brought-- the higher
factions brought that with them

00:44:55.360 --> 00:44:56.449 align:middle line:90%
to that region as well.

00:44:56.449 --> 00:44:58.240 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And the Templars
picked up on that

00:44:58.240 --> 00:44:59.948 align:middle line:84%
because they were
friends with the Arabs.

00:44:59.948 --> 00:45:01.390 align:middle line:90%
They all got along just fine.

00:45:01.390 --> 00:45:01.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:45:01.590 --> 00:45:03.090 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And the
gnostic Christians.

00:45:03.090 --> 00:45:05.620 align:middle line:84%
They got along just fine with
the Arabs and the Muslims.

00:45:05.620 --> 00:45:07.869 align:middle line:84%
And that they basically
brought all this understanding

00:45:07.869 --> 00:45:08.780 align:middle line:90%
into Europe.

00:45:08.780 --> 00:45:11.970 align:middle line:84%
So it's thanks to the
Templars, essentially,

00:45:11.970 --> 00:45:15.260 align:middle line:84%
and the Cistercians, who
basically brought this in

00:45:15.260 --> 00:45:17.774 align:middle line:84%
via, and through, the
construct of Gothic cathedrals.

00:45:17.774 --> 00:45:19.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I was
just going to say.

00:45:19.190 --> 00:45:20.200 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It's essentially--
the Gothic art

00:45:20.200 --> 00:45:22.400 align:middle line:84%
is essentially the mirror
image of the Arabic art.

00:45:22.400 --> 00:45:23.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:45:23.200 --> 00:45:26.110 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So they were
light years ahead--

00:45:26.110 --> 00:45:26.969 align:middle line:90%
the Arabs were.

00:45:26.969 --> 00:45:29.260 align:middle line:84%
Because they had already had
contact with the Libraries

00:45:29.260 --> 00:45:30.297 align:middle line:90%
of Alexandria.

00:45:30.297 --> 00:45:31.630 align:middle line:90%
They'd come from that tradition.

00:45:31.630 --> 00:45:33.430 align:middle line:84%
They'd come from the
Mandaean tradition.

00:45:33.430 --> 00:45:36.350 align:middle line:84%
People who were literally light
years ahead of anybody else.

00:45:36.350 --> 00:45:38.860 align:middle line:84%
And they used the
Templars as a way

00:45:38.860 --> 00:45:40.965 align:middle line:84%
to actually put
this into Europe.

00:45:40.965 --> 00:45:42.340 align:middle line:84%
So there's a
wonderful connection

00:45:42.340 --> 00:45:43.540 align:middle line:90%
between all of these people.

00:45:43.540 --> 00:45:44.670 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of documents
support the concepts.

00:45:44.670 --> 00:45:45.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: At the higher levels.

00:45:45.910 --> 00:45:47.020 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: At the very high level.

00:45:47.020 --> 00:45:49.020 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But when you
go down to the masses who

00:45:49.020 --> 00:45:51.670 align:middle line:84%
were hungry, and
educated, it doesn't

00:45:51.670 --> 00:45:52.840 align:middle line:90%
matter what side you're on.

00:45:52.840 --> 00:45:53.817 align:middle line:90%
It's just ugly.

00:45:53.817 --> 00:45:54.775 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: It's survival.

00:45:54.775 --> 00:45:55.620 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's just survival.

00:45:55.620 --> 00:45:57.190 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And it's also
dogma, and it's also--

00:45:57.190 --> 00:45:57.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is.

00:45:57.590 --> 00:45:58.330 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: --propaganda.

00:45:58.330 --> 00:45:58.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Now--

00:45:58.600 --> 00:45:59.470 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Kind of
like today, actually.

00:45:59.470 --> 00:46:00.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Like today.

00:46:00.680 --> 00:46:01.930 align:middle line:90%
So let's bring the church in.

00:46:01.930 --> 00:46:05.540 align:middle line:84%
What was the pope's motivation,
then, for the Crusades?

00:46:05.540 --> 00:46:07.280 align:middle line:84%
And let's talk about
how these rag-tag--

00:46:07.280 --> 00:46:10.000 align:middle line:84%
this rag-tag
assemblage occurred.

00:46:10.000 --> 00:46:12.160 align:middle line:84%
Because this is where
some of the characters

00:46:12.160 --> 00:46:13.540 align:middle line:90%
start entering in.

00:46:13.540 --> 00:46:15.070 align:middle line:10%
Some of these
wonderful characters,

00:46:15.070 --> 00:46:16.702 align:middle line:10%
like Peter the Hermit.

00:46:16.702 --> 00:46:17.994 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:46:17.994 --> 00:46:19.660 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Peter the
Hermit, it turns out,

00:46:19.660 --> 00:46:21.730 align:middle line:84%
was one of the
original monks that

00:46:21.730 --> 00:46:24.260 align:middle line:84%
went, or vowed to take
care of this land that

00:46:24.260 --> 00:46:25.060 align:middle line:90%
was given to them.

00:46:25.060 --> 00:46:27.297 align:middle line:84%
He was one of the members
of the Order of Sion.

00:46:27.297 --> 00:46:29.630 align:middle line:84%
So it turns out that he was
actually the spiritual guide

00:46:29.630 --> 00:46:32.780 align:middle line:84%
to this young guy to become the
first patriarch of Jerusalem.

00:46:32.780 --> 00:46:34.720 align:middle line:84%
So talk about a
long relationship.

00:46:34.720 --> 00:46:40.870 align:middle line:84%
I always believed that the whole
idea for the pope encouraging

00:46:40.870 --> 00:46:43.270 align:middle line:84%
hundreds of thousands of
people to march on Jerusalem

00:46:43.270 --> 00:46:46.100 align:middle line:84%
was just the liberation
of the Holy Sepulcher.

00:46:46.100 --> 00:46:47.080 align:middle line:90%
I thought, OK.

00:46:47.080 --> 00:46:49.720 align:middle line:84%
Because we're now in a decade
where the Turks are not

00:46:49.720 --> 00:46:50.745 align:middle line:90%
allowing anybody in.

00:46:50.745 --> 00:46:52.870 align:middle line:84%
The Christians are not
being allowed in unless they

00:46:52.870 --> 00:46:53.890 align:middle line:90%
pay a lot of money.

00:46:53.890 --> 00:46:55.720 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of them
didn't even survive

00:46:55.720 --> 00:46:57.820 align:middle line:84%
getting to the Church
of Holy Sepulcher.

00:46:57.820 --> 00:46:59.170 align:middle line:90%
I can buy that.

00:46:59.170 --> 00:47:00.610 align:middle line:90%
But then I read something else.

00:47:00.610 --> 00:47:03.068 align:middle line:84%
That there was a lot of trouble
going on in Constantinople,

00:47:03.068 --> 00:47:05.830 align:middle line:90%
where the Emperor Comnenus who--

00:47:05.830 --> 00:47:07.780 align:middle line:90%
real untrustworthy guy.

00:47:07.780 --> 00:47:10.660 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this guy had a
multiple personality disorder.

00:47:10.660 --> 00:47:12.710 align:middle line:84%
It turns out that
he was friends--

00:47:12.710 --> 00:47:15.910 align:middle line:84%
in fact, the only friend
that he had was the pope.

00:47:15.910 --> 00:47:18.850 align:middle line:84%
And I think he persuaded the
pope to send an army his way,

00:47:18.850 --> 00:47:22.120 align:middle line:84%
to Constantinople, to fight
the Turks-- to remove them

00:47:22.120 --> 00:47:25.020 align:middle line:84%
from his land so they can
basically invade Turkey.

00:47:25.020 --> 00:47:27.460 align:middle line:84%
Or what would become
Turkey later on.

00:47:27.460 --> 00:47:30.160 align:middle line:84%
I think that that was part of
the motivation for the pope

00:47:30.160 --> 00:47:32.200 align:middle line:90%
actually going to the Holy Land.

00:47:32.200 --> 00:47:35.530 align:middle line:84%
There may have even been
two different concepts

00:47:35.530 --> 00:47:37.180 align:middle line:90%
going on here at the same time.

00:47:37.180 --> 00:47:39.160 align:middle line:84%
It seems as though
the army was sent over

00:47:39.160 --> 00:47:42.415 align:middle line:84%
to help Comnenus get
rid of his enemies.

00:47:42.415 --> 00:47:44.290 align:middle line:84%
But then they thought,
well, while we're here

00:47:44.290 --> 00:47:46.257 align:middle line:84%
we might as well get all
the way to Jerusalem.

00:47:46.257 --> 00:47:47.090 align:middle line:90%
It took him forever.

00:47:47.090 --> 00:47:48.044 align:middle line:90%
It took him years.

00:47:48.044 --> 00:47:49.960 align:middle line:84%
They were under the
impression that they would

00:47:49.960 --> 00:47:51.512 align:middle line:90%
take him a couple of weeks.

00:47:51.512 --> 00:47:53.470 align:middle line:84%
I have a letter from one
of the knights saying,

00:47:53.470 --> 00:47:55.180 align:middle line:84%
yeah-- they're
writing to his wife.

00:47:55.180 --> 00:47:57.640 align:middle line:84%
Oh, we're going to be in
Jerusalem in a couple of weeks.

00:47:57.640 --> 00:47:59.750 align:middle line:84%
Three years later
they finally arrived.

00:47:59.750 --> 00:48:02.170 align:middle line:84%
So it tells me that
the plan appears

00:48:02.170 --> 00:48:04.120 align:middle line:90%
to have changed on route.

00:48:04.120 --> 00:48:07.580 align:middle line:84%
Now, when the deed is
done and they finally

00:48:07.580 --> 00:48:10.810 align:middle line:84%
do get to Jerusalem, it
seems to me that the--

00:48:10.810 --> 00:48:13.210 align:middle line:84%
it took a while for
the pope to recognize

00:48:13.210 --> 00:48:15.640 align:middle line:84%
that there was something else
going on in Jerusalem, where

00:48:15.640 --> 00:48:18.160 align:middle line:84%
there's a group of guys who
are doing something very, very

00:48:18.160 --> 00:48:19.260 align:middle line:90%
mysterious.

00:48:19.260 --> 00:48:22.090 align:middle line:84%
And when you do something
behind closed doors

00:48:22.090 --> 00:48:23.620 align:middle line:84%
you want to know
what's going on.

00:48:23.620 --> 00:48:27.010 align:middle line:84%
So the pope was always five
steps behind this small group

00:48:27.010 --> 00:48:28.465 align:middle line:90%
of people--

00:48:28.465 --> 00:48:30.724 align:middle line:84%
about nine or 11
people-- or 11 Templars.

00:48:30.724 --> 00:48:32.890 align:middle line:84%
I've come to the conclusion
that there were actually

00:48:32.890 --> 00:48:35.430 align:middle line:84%
11 original people,
for good reason.

00:48:35.430 --> 00:48:37.480 align:middle line:84%
And there's documentation
to back it up.

00:48:37.480 --> 00:48:41.230 align:middle line:84%
But he was always
behind the times of what

00:48:41.230 --> 00:48:42.550 align:middle line:90%
the Templars were really up to.

00:48:42.550 --> 00:48:44.740 align:middle line:84%
Because by the time the
Templars are officially

00:48:44.740 --> 00:48:48.472 align:middle line:84%
ordained by the pope
in 1128, well, the news

00:48:48.472 --> 00:48:49.930 align:middle line:84%
has really been
out for a long time

00:48:49.930 --> 00:48:52.710 align:middle line:84%
that the Templars have been
around for at least 20 years.

00:48:52.710 --> 00:48:55.090 align:middle line:84%
Everybody is going, well, that
was a really boring story.

00:48:55.090 --> 00:48:56.280 align:middle line:84%
We know about the
Order of the Temple.

00:48:56.280 --> 00:48:57.640 align:middle line:90%
They've been around for years.

00:48:57.640 --> 00:49:00.275 align:middle line:84%
So the pope was trying
to get in on the act.

00:49:00.275 --> 00:49:02.650 align:middle line:84%
He was trying to muscle in on
what they were looking for.

00:49:02.650 --> 00:49:05.750 align:middle line:84%
Because the idea was that
they found this big treasure

00:49:05.750 --> 00:49:07.180 align:middle line:90%
underneath Temple Mount.

00:49:07.180 --> 00:49:09.190 align:middle line:84%
Of course, to most
people treasure

00:49:09.190 --> 00:49:12.440 align:middle line:84%
brings up money, riches, gold,
which brings up the point

00:49:12.440 --> 00:49:13.240 align:middle line:90%
again--

00:49:13.240 --> 00:49:15.415 align:middle line:84%
why would a bunch of
nobles travel all the way

00:49:15.415 --> 00:49:18.750 align:middle line:84%
to the Holy Land to dig tunnels
in inhospitable conditions

00:49:18.750 --> 00:49:20.022 align:middle line:90%
to look for money?

00:49:20.022 --> 00:49:21.480 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: When they
came from money

00:49:21.480 --> 00:49:23.100 align:middle line:84%
and they had already
disavowed it.

00:49:23.100 --> 00:49:25.980 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Stay at
home, keep the money,

00:49:25.980 --> 00:49:28.740 align:middle line:84%
put your feet up, and sit by
the fire and read a good book.

00:49:28.740 --> 00:49:30.940 align:middle line:84%
It's not difficult
to understand.

00:49:30.940 --> 00:49:32.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So aside
from these royals,

00:49:32.490 --> 00:49:34.800 align:middle line:84%
which have given it all up,
which are there searching

00:49:34.800 --> 00:49:37.740 align:middle line:84%
for something mysterious
under the Temple Mount--

00:49:37.740 --> 00:49:41.280 align:middle line:84%
which of course, the debate
still rages to this day

00:49:41.280 --> 00:49:42.930 align:middle line:90%
in certain ways--

00:49:42.930 --> 00:49:45.380 align:middle line:84%
you have other
characters that enter in.

00:49:45.380 --> 00:49:48.390 align:middle line:84%
Extreme ascetics such
as Peter the Hermit.

00:49:48.390 --> 00:49:51.250 align:middle line:84%
Now how does he start
factoring into this story?

00:49:51.250 --> 00:49:52.050 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh.

00:49:52.050 --> 00:49:53.760 align:middle line:84%
They're all into
extreme asceticism.

00:49:53.760 --> 00:49:55.636 align:middle line:84%
They're trying to
out-asceticize each other--

00:49:55.636 --> 00:49:56.510 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, my God.

00:49:56.510 --> 00:49:58.204 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: --if that's
even an adjective.

00:49:58.204 --> 00:50:00.370 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they're literally
trying to outdo themselves

00:50:00.370 --> 00:50:00.860 align:middle line:84%
at being more poor
than anybody else.

00:50:00.860 --> 00:50:02.193 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I'm sleeping on straw.

00:50:02.193 --> 00:50:03.380 align:middle line:90%
Well, I'm sleeping on dirt.

00:50:03.380 --> 00:50:05.380 align:middle line:90%
Well, I'm sleeping in a bog.

00:50:05.380 --> 00:50:08.470 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I'm going to
sleep in the woods.

00:50:08.470 --> 00:50:09.485 align:middle line:90%
They were quite funny.

00:50:09.485 --> 00:50:11.360 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's Walter
the Penniless as well.

00:50:11.360 --> 00:50:12.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:50:12.060 --> 00:50:12.960 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: All these
people suddenly

00:50:12.960 --> 00:50:14.460 align:middle line:84%
renounced their
worldly possessions

00:50:14.460 --> 00:50:15.793 align:middle line:90%
to go on this spiritual journey.

00:50:15.793 --> 00:50:17.340 align:middle line:84%
And Peter the
Hermit, it turns out,

00:50:17.340 --> 00:50:18.790 align:middle line:84%
was actually very
central to the story.

00:50:18.790 --> 00:50:19.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:50:19.290 --> 00:50:21.456 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Because he was one
of the original founders

00:50:21.456 --> 00:50:25.110 align:middle line:84%
of this Order of Sion,
that is so mysterious.

00:50:25.110 --> 00:50:28.170 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, when
the Crusades end up

00:50:28.170 --> 00:50:32.370 align:middle line:84%
in Jerusalem, and the Templars,
and the Order of the Knights

00:50:32.370 --> 00:50:34.720 align:middle line:84%
of the Holy Sepulcher,
he basically

00:50:34.720 --> 00:50:38.130 align:middle line:84%
is given charge of
most of Jerusalem

00:50:38.130 --> 00:50:41.790 align:middle line:84%
when they basically go off and
do whatever they were doing

00:50:41.790 --> 00:50:44.340 align:middle line:90%
quietly outside of Jerusalem.

00:50:44.340 --> 00:50:46.560 align:middle line:84%
In terms of the Crusades,
it was mopping up the land,

00:50:46.560 --> 00:50:48.664 align:middle line:84%
and getting rid of
their Arab enemies.

00:50:48.664 --> 00:50:50.580 align:middle line:84%
And on the other side,
there was another group

00:50:50.580 --> 00:50:53.029 align:middle line:84%
of people doing something
else very secretly.

00:50:53.029 --> 00:50:55.320 align:middle line:84%
So it turns out he was actually
a very important person

00:50:55.320 --> 00:50:56.910 align:middle line:90%
in the big scheme of things.

00:50:56.910 --> 00:51:00.390 align:middle line:84%
And he eventually
decides to take back

00:51:00.390 --> 00:51:04.920 align:middle line:84%
what he learns, in terms of
spiritual angle in Jerusalem,

00:51:04.920 --> 00:51:07.020 align:middle line:84%
and goes back to
Europe and founds

00:51:07.020 --> 00:51:09.630 align:middle line:84%
his own particular school,
based on the principles

00:51:09.630 --> 00:51:11.040 align:middle line:90%
of John the Baptist.

00:51:11.040 --> 00:51:14.020 align:middle line:84%
So here's a guy
who has written--

00:51:14.020 --> 00:51:16.660 align:middle line:84%
he's like a little minuscule
sideline in history.

00:51:16.660 --> 00:51:19.040 align:middle line:84%
And yet, he is so important
in the big scheme of things.

00:51:19.040 --> 00:51:21.390 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Who had a lot
of influence and power.

00:51:21.390 --> 00:51:23.100 align:middle line:84%
It sounds like he
was revered, and had

00:51:23.100 --> 00:51:24.360 align:middle line:90%
great levels of respect--

00:51:24.360 --> 00:51:24.970 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, very much so.

00:51:24.970 --> 00:51:26.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Among the
high and low circles.

00:51:26.890 --> 00:51:27.889 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: He was the top.

00:51:27.889 --> 00:51:29.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Plucking
hairs off his donkey--

00:51:29.820 --> 00:51:30.620 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:51:30.620 --> 00:51:32.355 align:middle line:84%
--just to have a
little piece of him.

00:51:32.355 --> 00:51:33.729 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: He was
so holy that they

00:51:33.729 --> 00:51:35.315 align:middle line:90%
plucked the hairs off his mule.

00:51:35.315 --> 00:51:37.647 align:middle line:84%
I get the vision
of watching that.

00:51:37.647 --> 00:51:39.480 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's like, do
you want my autograph?

00:51:39.480 --> 00:51:40.280 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:51:40.280 --> 00:51:41.730 align:middle line:90%
We want a hair off your mule.

00:51:41.730 --> 00:51:42.540 align:middle line:90%
It's hysterical.

00:51:42.540 --> 00:51:42.870 align:middle line:90%
But no.

00:51:42.870 --> 00:51:43.670 align:middle line:90%
He was.

00:51:43.670 --> 00:51:46.180 align:middle line:84%
He was revered because he was
actually walking the talk.

00:51:46.180 --> 00:51:47.891 align:middle line:90%
He was doing real Christianity.

00:51:47.891 --> 00:51:49.890 align:middle line:84%
Not what the Catholic
Church had turned it into.

00:51:49.890 --> 00:51:51.330 align:middle line:84%
And that's why he
was appreciated.

00:51:51.330 --> 00:51:52.914 align:middle line:84%
Because there was
an undercurrent

00:51:52.914 --> 00:51:54.330 align:middle line:84%
in Europe of people
who understood

00:51:54.330 --> 00:51:56.825 align:middle line:84%
the real message
of Christianity,

00:51:56.825 --> 00:51:58.200 align:middle line:84%
which is not the
message that was

00:51:58.200 --> 00:52:00.020 align:middle line:90%
being promoted by the church.

00:52:00.020 --> 00:52:01.450 align:middle line:90%
Not in any way imaginable.

00:52:01.450 --> 00:52:04.460 align:middle line:84%
This is why I never confuse
Christianity with Catholicism.

00:52:04.460 --> 00:52:07.030 align:middle line:84%
The two are very
different to each other.

00:52:07.030 --> 00:52:08.850 align:middle line:84%
In fact, early
Christianity is almost

00:52:08.850 --> 00:52:10.690 align:middle line:90%
like a version of Buddhism.

00:52:10.690 --> 00:52:11.840 align:middle line:90%
Zen.

00:52:11.840 --> 00:52:13.065 align:middle line:90%
Not dissimilar.

00:52:13.065 --> 00:52:16.500 align:middle line:84%
Not dissimilar from
esoteric Islam, either.

00:52:16.500 --> 00:52:18.450 align:middle line:84%
They're all pretty
much the same thing.

00:52:18.450 --> 00:52:20.160 align:middle line:84%
So he was actually
practicing this.

00:52:20.160 --> 00:52:23.380 align:middle line:84%
He put his life on the line, put
his money aside, and actually

00:52:23.380 --> 00:52:24.180 align:middle line:90%
went there.

00:52:24.180 --> 00:52:27.060 align:middle line:84%
And he nearly died on
the way to Palestine.

00:52:27.060 --> 00:52:29.280 align:middle line:84%
Ironically, the guy that
picks him up off the ground,

00:52:29.280 --> 00:52:33.120 align:middle line:84%
literally, finds his emaciated
body on the road to Jerusalem,

00:52:33.120 --> 00:52:34.120 align:middle line:90%
is Godfrey de Bouillon--

00:52:34.120 --> 00:52:36.245 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's who I was
going to ask about next.

00:52:36.245 --> 00:52:38.760 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: --the young man who
was taught by Peter the Hermit.

00:52:38.760 --> 00:52:40.565 align:middle line:84%
It sounds like-- the whole
thing sounds like a premeditated

00:52:40.565 --> 00:52:40.990 align:middle line:90%
plan--

00:52:40.990 --> 00:52:41.177 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Ohh.

00:52:41.177 --> 00:52:41.290 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:52:41.290 --> 00:52:41.440 align:middle line:90%
Can I read--

00:52:41.440 --> 00:52:42.620 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: --because
I think it was.

00:52:42.620 --> 00:52:44.710 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I'm just going to read
some of his traits just to--

00:52:44.710 --> 00:52:45.870 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, absolutely.

00:52:45.870 --> 00:52:47.260 align:middle line:90%
This could take an hour.

00:52:47.260 --> 00:52:48.060 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:52:48.060 --> 00:52:50.210 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, this
is his resume, right?

00:52:50.210 --> 00:52:51.877 align:middle line:84%
Godfrey-- "God-fray"
de Bouillon, right?

00:52:51.877 --> 00:52:53.085 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Godfrey de Bouillon.

00:52:53.085 --> 00:52:54.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:52:54.090 --> 00:52:59.640 align:middle line:84%
"Tall, blond, bearded, pious,
humble, gentle, generous.

00:52:59.640 --> 00:53:00.960 align:middle line:90%
A model knight.

00:53:00.960 --> 00:53:02.640 align:middle line:90%
Virtuous."

00:53:02.640 --> 00:53:05.280 align:middle line:84%
Really, it almost sounds like
the Knights at the Round Table.

00:53:05.280 --> 00:53:07.830 align:middle line:84%
Combination of Lancelot
and Arthur, right?

00:53:07.830 --> 00:53:11.220 align:middle line:84%
"He was named King of Jerusalem,
but actually refused."

00:53:11.220 --> 00:53:12.642 align:middle line:90%
So let's go on from there.

00:53:12.642 --> 00:53:14.850 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about who this
character was, because he's

00:53:14.850 --> 00:53:16.382 align:middle line:90%
so central to the story.

00:53:16.382 --> 00:53:17.340 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: It turns out--

00:53:17.340 --> 00:53:19.810 align:middle line:84%
I think that-- and there
are echoes of this.

00:53:19.810 --> 00:53:20.880 align:middle line:84%
And again, when you're
dealing with something

00:53:20.880 --> 00:53:22.530 align:middle line:84%
as precious as the
holy bloodline that

00:53:22.530 --> 00:53:25.140 align:middle line:84%
has been persecuted for
1,000 years in Europe,

00:53:25.140 --> 00:53:26.977 align:middle line:84%
you don't draw
attention to yourself.

00:53:26.977 --> 00:53:29.310 align:middle line:84%
But again, it's something
that I brought up in the book,

00:53:29.310 --> 00:53:32.790 align:middle line:84%
and that Henry Lincoln and
company had also brought up

00:53:32.790 --> 00:53:34.290 align:middle line:84%
in the "Holy Blood,
Holy Grail"--

00:53:34.290 --> 00:53:36.560 align:middle line:84%
was that there are echoes
of the fact that Godfrey de

00:53:36.560 --> 00:53:37.976 align:middle line:84%
Bouillon appears
to have been part

00:53:37.976 --> 00:53:39.990 align:middle line:90%
out of this holy bloodline.

00:53:39.990 --> 00:53:42.630 align:middle line:84%
Why else were these monks sort
of moved halfway across Europe

00:53:42.630 --> 00:53:45.120 align:middle line:84%
to groom a young
man, who had become

00:53:45.120 --> 00:53:47.277 align:middle line:90%
the custodian of Jerusalem?

00:53:47.277 --> 00:53:49.860 align:middle line:84%
Because when you actually look
at the paperwork that survives,

00:53:49.860 --> 00:53:53.640 align:middle line:84%
it turns out that when the
initiation ceremony was done

00:53:53.640 --> 00:53:58.230 align:middle line:84%
to put Godfrey on the
throne, and his brothers--

00:53:58.230 --> 00:54:00.150 align:middle line:84%
because he died
there shortly after--

00:54:00.150 --> 00:54:00.290 align:middle line:90%
they were all--

00:54:00.290 --> 00:54:01.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He was
poisoned, right?

00:54:01.200 --> 00:54:01.700 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: --done.

00:54:01.700 --> 00:54:03.225 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He was
poisoned, right?

00:54:03.225 --> 00:54:03.720 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Um--

00:54:03.720 --> 00:54:03.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Was he poisoned?

00:54:03.820 --> 00:54:04.110 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: No.

00:54:04.110 --> 00:54:05.349 align:middle line:90%
He died a normal death.

00:54:05.349 --> 00:54:06.390 align:middle line:90%
The others were poisoned.

00:54:06.390 --> 00:54:07.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, the
others were poisoned.

00:54:07.050 --> 00:54:08.250 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Although it
gets very confusing.

00:54:08.250 --> 00:54:08.745 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I'm confused.

00:54:08.745 --> 00:54:09.030 align:middle line:90%
But go ahead.

00:54:09.030 --> 00:54:09.310 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: I know.

00:54:09.310 --> 00:54:10.143 align:middle line:90%
It's very confusing.

00:54:10.143 --> 00:54:11.010 align:middle line:90%
They all died.

00:54:11.010 --> 00:54:12.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, they died.

00:54:12.010 --> 00:54:13.360 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Everybody dies.

00:54:13.360 --> 00:54:15.780 align:middle line:84%
But the ceremonies were
always conducted on land

00:54:15.780 --> 00:54:17.560 align:middle line:90%
owned by the Order of Sion.

00:54:17.560 --> 00:54:18.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:54:18.630 --> 00:54:21.600 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And it was always said
that Godfrey owed his throne

00:54:21.600 --> 00:54:22.506 align:middle line:90%
to the Order of Sion.

00:54:22.506 --> 00:54:24.380 align:middle line:84%
And it's something you
hear again, and again,

00:54:24.380 --> 00:54:26.320 align:middle line:84%
throughout the
Templars story as well.

00:54:26.320 --> 00:54:28.680 align:middle line:84%
Not just in Jerusalem,
but also in Portugal.

00:54:28.680 --> 00:54:32.340 align:middle line:84%
They owed their position
to the Order of Sion.

00:54:32.340 --> 00:54:34.190 align:middle line:90%
So they owed him a favor.

00:54:34.190 --> 00:54:36.000 align:middle line:90%
Not as though their--

00:54:36.000 --> 00:54:37.680 align:middle line:84%
they have to have
sort of paid him dues.

00:54:37.680 --> 00:54:40.710 align:middle line:84%
But they are obligated to
repay a certain favor in order

00:54:40.710 --> 00:54:43.380 align:middle line:84%
to keep a certain
connection, and transaction

00:54:43.380 --> 00:54:44.994 align:middle line:90%
going between the two groups.

00:54:44.994 --> 00:54:46.410 align:middle line:84%
And I found that
very interesting.

00:54:46.410 --> 00:54:48.150 align:middle line:84%
So it turns out
that here we have

00:54:48.150 --> 00:54:51.130 align:middle line:84%
the inklings of a bloodline
that was kept very quiet,

00:54:51.130 --> 00:54:51.930 align:middle line:90%
very on the ground.

00:54:51.930 --> 00:54:54.010 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, window of
opportunity comes up.

00:54:54.010 --> 00:54:54.810 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:54:54.810 --> 00:54:56.351 align:middle line:84%
Let's put him in
Jerusalem, and we'll

00:54:56.351 --> 00:54:58.020 align:middle line:90%
get the ball rolling from there.

00:54:58.020 --> 00:55:01.440 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And how did the pope
and the church relate to him?

00:55:01.440 --> 00:55:02.690 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Not well.

00:55:02.690 --> 00:55:03.600 align:middle line:90%
They kind of--

00:55:03.600 --> 00:55:05.580 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they were sort
of trying to figure out

00:55:05.580 --> 00:55:07.080 align:middle line:90%
where this is all going.

00:55:07.080 --> 00:55:10.770 align:middle line:84%
Because they tried to put
such a big stamp on top

00:55:10.770 --> 00:55:15.150 align:middle line:84%
of the holy bloodline, and try
to miniaturize it to the point

00:55:15.150 --> 00:55:17.450 align:middle line:90%
where they would--

00:55:17.450 --> 00:55:19.710 align:middle line:84%
these people were described
as great faith-healers.

00:55:19.710 --> 00:55:21.700 align:middle line:90%
And also great mystics.

00:55:21.700 --> 00:55:25.170 align:middle line:84%
At this point you have a group
of monks sitting in an office.

00:55:25.170 --> 00:55:27.030 align:middle line:84%
I believe it was
somewhere in Ireland.

00:55:27.030 --> 00:55:29.370 align:middle line:84%
And they were actually
told to create the story

00:55:29.370 --> 00:55:32.970 align:middle line:84%
to deminiaturize this
holy bloodline by turning

00:55:32.970 --> 00:55:34.860 align:middle line:84%
into fairies, and to
supernatural beings.

00:55:34.860 --> 00:55:36.194 align:middle line:90%
That they weren't actually real.

00:55:36.194 --> 00:55:37.859 align:middle line:84%
This is where the
concept of the fairies

00:55:37.859 --> 00:55:39.568 align:middle line:84%
actually comes from--
in the Middle Ages.

00:55:39.568 --> 00:55:41.483 align:middle line:84%
Because fairies are
supposed to be bad people.

00:55:41.483 --> 00:55:43.410 align:middle line:84%
If you're affected by
fairies in your dreams,

00:55:43.410 --> 00:55:45.190 align:middle line:90%
that's the devil talking to you.

00:55:45.190 --> 00:55:47.130 align:middle line:84%
And there are these
supposed people

00:55:47.130 --> 00:55:48.840 align:middle line:84%
that come from a
divine source, that

00:55:48.840 --> 00:55:51.270 align:middle line:84%
pretend to be humans,
that are bad people

00:55:51.270 --> 00:55:53.820 align:middle line:84%
because they associate with
fairies and little people.

00:55:53.820 --> 00:55:56.440 align:middle line:84%
And that's those-- the
church's PR department,

00:55:56.440 --> 00:55:58.700 align:middle line:84%
what becomes the
Holy Inquisition--

00:55:58.700 --> 00:56:01.950 align:middle line:84%
are trying to educate
the public that anything

00:56:01.950 --> 00:56:04.370 align:middle line:84%
to do with the holy bloodline--
if you hear about this,

00:56:04.370 --> 00:56:06.540 align:middle line:84%
or see anything, you
come and talk to us.

00:56:06.540 --> 00:56:07.780 align:middle line:90%
And we'll take care of it.

00:56:07.780 --> 00:56:09.750 align:middle line:84%
That's how they worked,
to try and make sure

00:56:09.750 --> 00:56:13.559 align:middle line:84%
that the lid was kept firmly on
this people who had the right--

00:56:13.559 --> 00:56:14.642 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: With the masses.

00:56:14.642 --> 00:56:16.350 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: --to rule by
divine appointment.

00:56:16.350 --> 00:56:17.210 align:middle line:90%
Not the church.

00:56:17.210 --> 00:56:19.209 align:middle line:84%
They had inserted themselves
into this position.

00:56:19.209 --> 00:56:22.339 align:middle line:84%
And now find themselves in the
terrible position of keeping

00:56:22.339 --> 00:56:23.630 align:middle line:90%
track, and a lid on everything.

00:56:23.630 --> 00:56:25.838 align:middle line:84%
And of course, the whole
thing was blowing wide open,

00:56:25.838 --> 00:56:27.450 align:middle line:84%
because of the
influential people

00:56:27.450 --> 00:56:29.040 align:middle line:90%
that had moved into Jerusalem.

00:56:29.040 --> 00:56:31.507 align:middle line:84%
And positioned themselves
outside of the church.

00:56:31.507 --> 00:56:32.340 align:middle line:90%
They had no control.

00:56:32.340 --> 00:56:34.315 align:middle line:84%
The church had no control
over these people.

00:56:34.315 --> 00:56:35.940 align:middle line:84%
That's why there were
always five steps

00:56:35.940 --> 00:56:37.440 align:middle line:90%
behind what they were doing.

00:56:37.440 --> 00:56:40.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And also, Godfrey's--

00:56:40.380 --> 00:56:44.280 align:middle line:84%
his mission was dedicated
to Our Lady, right?

00:56:44.280 --> 00:56:45.805 align:middle line:90%
He was very ordered toward--

00:56:45.805 --> 00:56:46.058 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, absolutely.

00:56:46.058 --> 00:56:46.800 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: --our lady.

00:56:46.800 --> 00:56:47.270 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Absolutely.

00:56:47.270 --> 00:56:48.070 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:56:48.070 --> 00:56:49.410 align:middle line:90%
So we just accept that.

00:56:49.410 --> 00:56:50.810 align:middle line:90%
Now let's go to Hugues.

00:56:50.810 --> 00:56:54.580 align:middle line:84%
And let's talk about how he
interfaces in this story.

00:56:54.580 --> 00:56:58.050 align:middle line:84%
Because the way the characters
all come together is very--

00:56:58.050 --> 00:56:59.245 align:middle line:90%
it's a tangled web.

00:56:59.245 --> 00:57:00.120 align:middle line:90%
It's confusing to me.

00:57:00.120 --> 00:57:01.125 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Appropriate.

00:57:01.125 --> 00:57:01.925 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:57:01.925 --> 00:57:04.210 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And also
somewhat designed.

00:57:04.210 --> 00:57:06.950 align:middle line:84%
Hugues de Payens
was, again, a noble.

00:57:06.950 --> 00:57:09.900 align:middle line:84%
He had extensive
connections to people

00:57:09.900 --> 00:57:12.069 align:middle line:84%
in Burgundy, who turns
out were all connected

00:57:12.069 --> 00:57:13.110 align:middle line:90%
to this divine bloodline.

00:57:13.110 --> 00:57:16.200 align:middle line:84%
They were all part of the
offshoots of these families.

00:57:16.200 --> 00:57:17.950 align:middle line:84%
And not much is
written about him.

00:57:17.950 --> 00:57:19.530 align:middle line:84%
Maybe because it
was never written.

00:57:19.530 --> 00:57:21.590 align:middle line:84%
Or because the
information is now lost,

00:57:21.590 --> 00:57:23.910 align:middle line:84%
as it tends to be of
the times of warfare.

00:57:23.910 --> 00:57:25.410 align:middle line:84%
But what we do know
is that he spent

00:57:25.410 --> 00:57:29.152 align:middle line:84%
a lot of his formative
years being groomed by one

00:57:29.152 --> 00:57:30.360 align:middle line:90%
of the members of his family.

00:57:30.360 --> 00:57:31.980 align:middle line:84%
I believe it was
his grandfather, who

00:57:31.980 --> 00:57:33.000 align:middle line:90%
was a great mystic.

00:57:33.000 --> 00:57:34.860 align:middle line:84%
And also had a great
appreciation for Arabic

00:57:34.860 --> 00:57:35.820 align:middle line:90%
culture.

00:57:35.820 --> 00:57:40.200 align:middle line:84%
And he said, actually, my
grandson, the Christian belief

00:57:40.200 --> 00:57:41.250 align:middle line:90%
and the Muslim belief--

00:57:41.250 --> 00:57:42.214 align:middle line:90%
it is the same thing.

00:57:42.214 --> 00:57:44.130 align:middle line:84%
So why don't you go walk
about the Middle East

00:57:44.130 --> 00:57:45.250 align:middle line:90%
and discover yourself.

00:57:45.250 --> 00:57:46.830 align:middle line:84%
And that's apparently
what he did.

00:57:46.830 --> 00:57:50.240 align:middle line:84%
So in 1100 and 1104, we
find Hugues de Payens

00:57:50.240 --> 00:57:53.160 align:middle line:84%
suddenly appearing
mysteriously in Jerusalem,

00:57:53.160 --> 00:57:56.460 align:middle line:84%
talking to other members of
the-- now the Proto-Templars.

00:57:56.460 --> 00:57:59.310 align:middle line:84%
And hanging out with the
people that come from Burgundy.

00:57:59.310 --> 00:58:00.720 align:middle line:90%
And Godfrey de Bouillon.

00:58:00.720 --> 00:58:04.350 align:middle line:84%
And also a bunch of people
that cruised all the way over

00:58:04.350 --> 00:58:07.470 align:middle line:84%
from this county, on the
opposite side of Europe

00:58:07.470 --> 00:58:09.040 align:middle line:90%
called Portugale.

00:58:09.040 --> 00:58:11.680 align:middle line:84%
They suddenly appear in
Jerusalem at the same time.

00:58:11.680 --> 00:58:13.710 align:middle line:10%
A big opportune
moment of meeting

00:58:13.710 --> 00:58:17.370 align:middle line:10%
of people, all of whose
roots go back to Burgundy.

00:58:17.370 --> 00:58:19.200 align:middle line:84%
So they all stretch
out throughout Europe

00:58:19.200 --> 00:58:22.050 align:middle line:84%
all the way to the
far west, and in 1104

00:58:22.050 --> 00:58:25.170 align:middle line:84%
they suddenly appear,
magically, in the same place.

00:58:25.170 --> 00:58:26.460 align:middle line:90%
All talking to each other.

00:58:26.460 --> 00:58:28.770 align:middle line:84%
All have the same
idea of creating

00:58:28.770 --> 00:58:31.474 align:middle line:84%
a kingdom of conscience,
as far from Rome

00:58:31.474 --> 00:58:32.640 align:middle line:90%
as you could possibly do it.

00:58:32.640 --> 00:58:35.610 align:middle line:10%
So you can just imagine
sitting down in Jerusalem--

00:58:35.610 --> 00:58:37.870 align:middle line:10%
there's still the
smoldering, ashes of battle--

00:58:37.870 --> 00:58:39.480 align:middle line:10%
sitting in a cafe
and going, you know,

00:58:39.480 --> 00:58:42.480 align:middle line:10%
it would be such a great idea
if we found the plot of land

00:58:42.480 --> 00:58:45.480 align:middle line:10%
somewhere as far away
from Rome as possible,

00:58:45.480 --> 00:58:48.000 align:middle line:10%
and create a real true
kingdom of conscience.

00:58:48.000 --> 00:58:48.900 align:middle line:90%
Real Christianity.

00:58:48.900 --> 00:58:50.760 align:middle line:84%
Real spirituality,
where we could

00:58:50.760 --> 00:58:54.670 align:middle line:84%
really embody the ideals and
aspirations of all people.

00:58:54.670 --> 00:58:56.440 align:middle line:84%
So that we can
all rise together.

00:58:56.440 --> 00:58:57.990 align:middle line:90%
Wouldn't this be a great idea?

00:58:57.990 --> 00:59:00.031 align:middle line:84%
And you can just imagine
having this conversation

00:59:00.031 --> 00:59:02.730 align:middle line:84%
and going, actually,
I know someone

00:59:02.730 --> 00:59:04.054 align:middle line:90%
who just came in on a boat.

00:59:04.054 --> 00:59:05.220 align:middle line:90%
They've got a piece of land.

00:59:05.220 --> 00:59:06.630 align:middle line:90%
And they come from my hometown.

00:59:06.630 --> 00:59:06.920 align:middle line:90%
Really?

00:59:06.920 --> 00:59:07.290 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:59:07.290 --> 00:59:08.430 align:middle line:90%
In fact, they're your cousins.

00:59:08.430 --> 00:59:09.230 align:middle line:90%
Really?

00:59:09.230 --> 00:59:10.290 align:middle line:90%
And he's my uncle.

00:59:10.290 --> 00:59:11.998 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, all
those people are either

00:59:11.998 --> 00:59:14.176 align:middle line:84%
uncles, cousins,
or some relation

00:59:14.176 --> 00:59:15.300 align:middle line:90%
to all of these bloodlines.

00:59:15.300 --> 00:59:17.340 align:middle line:84%
And all of these
people in Burgundy

00:59:17.340 --> 00:59:21.240 align:middle line:84%
who are very influential
in creating organizations

00:59:21.240 --> 00:59:22.620 align:middle line:90%
from scratch.

00:59:22.620 --> 00:59:25.440 align:middle line:84%
And in 1104 they're
all in the same place,

00:59:25.440 --> 00:59:27.180 align:middle line:90%
hatching a big plot.

00:59:27.180 --> 00:59:30.030 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then another man,
a very important character,

00:59:30.030 --> 00:59:31.430 align:middle line:90%
Bernard de Clairvaux comes in.

00:59:31.430 --> 00:59:32.310 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh.

00:59:32.310 --> 00:59:33.601 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And so you know what?

00:59:33.601 --> 00:59:34.540 align:middle line:90%
We're out of time.

00:59:34.540 --> 00:59:36.704 align:middle line:84%
We're going to pick it
up with the development

00:59:36.704 --> 00:59:38.370 align:middle line:84%
of this cast of
characters just a little

00:59:38.370 --> 00:59:40.820 align:middle line:84%
bit more so that people get
the nature of the group that

00:59:40.820 --> 00:59:41.620 align:middle line:90%
had assembled--

00:59:41.620 --> 00:59:42.480 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: He's the man.

00:59:42.480 --> 00:59:43.438 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: He's the man.

00:59:43.438 --> 00:59:46.250 align:middle line:84%
So we'll save the man for
the next conversation.

00:59:46.250 --> 00:59:47.700 align:middle line:90%
So OK?

00:59:47.700 --> 00:59:48.927 align:middle line:90%
We'll remember where we are?

00:59:48.927 --> 00:59:50.760 align:middle line:84%
Because we're only like
a quarter of the way

00:59:50.760 --> 00:59:52.176 align:middle line:84%
through all of
this at this point.

00:59:52.176 --> 00:59:53.490 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh my god.

00:59:53.490 --> 00:59:56.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: In part 2 of our
story we go back to Jerusalem,

00:59:56.130 --> 00:59:58.650 align:middle line:84%
and dig under the Temple
Mount with the Templar.

00:59:58.650 --> 01:00:01.140 align:middle line:84%
There's a reason that
kings and popes alike

01:00:01.140 --> 01:00:04.620 align:middle line:84%
gave the Templars vast tracts
of land, gold, and silver.

01:00:04.620 --> 01:00:05.864 align:middle line:90%
What did they possess?

